1
00:03:50,020 --> 00:03:54,620
I have sailed the world
Beheld its wonders

2
00:03:54,730 --> 00:03:59,260
From the Dardanelles
To the mountains of Peru

3
00:03:59,370 --> 00:04:03,570
But there's no place like London

4
00:04:03,670 --> 00:04:07,700
No, there's no place like London

5
00:04:07,810 --> 00:04:09,210
Mr. Todd?

6
00:04:10,140 --> 00:04:14,710
You are young
Life has been kind to you

7
00:04:18,120 --> 00:04:22,490
You will learn

8
00:04:37,270 --> 00:04:39,330
There's a hole in the world
like a great black pit

9
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:41,310
And the vermin of the world inhabit it

10
00:04:41,410 --> 00:04:43,430
And its morals aren't worth
what a pig could spit

11
00:04:43,540 --> 00:04:46,040
And it goes by the name of London

12
00:04:47,180 --> 00:04:49,240
At the top of the hole
sit a privileged few

13
00:04:49,350 --> 00:04:51,250
Making mock of the vermin
in the lower zoo

14
00:04:51,350 --> 00:04:53,080
Turning beauty into filth and greed

15
00:04:53,190 --> 00:04:58,490
I too have sailed the world
and seen its wonders

16
00:04:58,590 --> 00:05:03,090
For the cruelty of men
is as wondrous as Peru

17
00:05:03,200 --> 00:05:07,460
But there's no place like London

18
00:05:25,320 --> 00:05:27,790
Is everything all right, Mr. Todd?

19
00:05:29,090 --> 00:05:31,390
I beg your indulgence, Anthony.

20
00:05:32,060 --> 00:05:34,220
My mind is far from easy.

21
00:05:36,200 --> 00:05:41,360
In these once familiar streets
I feel shadows everywhere.

22
00:05:41,640 --> 00:05:42,970
Shadows?

23
00:05:44,510 --> 00:05:45,800
Ghosts.

24
00:05:53,050 --> 00:05:56,610
There was a barber and his wife

25
00:05:56,720 --> 00:05:59,650
And she was beautiful

26
00:06:00,820 --> 00:06:04,190
A foolish barber and his wife

27
00:06:04,290 --> 00:06:07,320
She was his reason and his life

28
00:06:07,430 --> 00:06:10,590
And she was beautiful

29
00:06:11,300 --> 00:06:15,170
And she was virtuous

30
00:06:17,210 --> 00:06:19,800
And he was

31
00:06:22,010 --> 00:06:25,540
naive

32
00:06:33,190 --> 00:06:36,680
There was another man who saw

33
00:06:36,790 --> 00:06:39,820
that she was beautiful

34
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:44,030
A pious vulture of the law

35
00:06:44,130 --> 00:06:47,500
Who, with a gesture of his claw

36
00:06:47,600 --> 00:06:51,130
Removed the barber from his plate

37
00:06:51,240 --> 00:06:55,730
Then there was nothing but to wait

38
00:06:55,840 --> 00:06:58,240
And she would fall

39
00:06:58,350 --> 00:07:04,750
So soft, so young
so lost and, oh, so beautiful

40
00:07:08,620 --> 00:07:11,720
And the lady, sir, did she succumb?

41
00:07:12,730 --> 00:07:16,190
Oh, that was many years ago

42
00:07:19,900 --> 00:07:23,230
I doubt if anyone would know

43
00:07:32,350 --> 00:07:34,110
I'd like to thank you, Anthony.

44
00:07:34,220 --> 00:07:38,240
If you hadn't spotted me,
I'd be lost on the ocean still.

45
00:07:39,450 --> 00:07:41,290
Will I see you again?

46
00:07:42,590 --> 00:07:44,920
You might find me if you like.

47
00:07:46,590 --> 00:07:49,430
Around Fleet Street, I wouldn't wonder.

48
00:07:51,200 --> 00:07:53,290
Until then, my friend.

49
00:08:03,540 --> 00:08:05,600
There's a hole in the world
like a great black pit

50
00:08:05,710 --> 00:08:07,770
And it's filled with people
who are filled with shit

51
00:08:07,880 --> 00:08:10,580
And the vermin of the world inhabit it

52
00:09:04,610 --> 00:09:05,630
A customer!

53
00:09:05,740 --> 00:09:07,500
Wait! What's your rush?
What's your hurry?

54
00:09:07,610 --> 00:09:09,840
You gave me such a fright
I thought you was a ghost!

55
00:09:09,940 --> 00:09:12,570
Half a minute, can't you sit?
Sit you down. Sit!

56
00:09:12,680 --> 00:09:15,170
All I meant is that I haven't seen
a customer for weeks!

57
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:17,750
Did you come here for a pie, sir?

58
00:09:17,850 --> 00:09:20,080
Do forgive me
if me head's a little vague

59
00:09:20,190 --> 00:09:21,180
What was that?

60
00:09:21,290 --> 00:09:24,990
But you'd think we had the plague!
From the way that people keep avoiding

61
00:09:25,090 --> 00:09:26,080
No, you don't.

62
00:09:26,190 --> 00:09:28,290
Heaven knows I try, sir!

63
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:31,060
But there's no one
comes in even to inhale

64
00:09:31,170 --> 00:09:33,900
Right you are, sir
would you like a drop of ale?

65
00:09:34,000 --> 00:09:37,160
Mind you, I can hardly blame them

66
00:09:37,270 --> 00:09:41,610
These are probably
the worst pies in London

67
00:09:41,710 --> 00:09:44,200
I know why nobody cares to take them

68
00:09:44,310 --> 00:09:47,540
I should know, I make them
But good? No!

69
00:09:47,650 --> 00:09:50,670
The worst pies in London

70
00:09:50,790 --> 00:09:54,650
Even that's polite
The worst pies in London

71
00:09:54,760 --> 00:09:57,250
If you doubt it, take a bite

72
00:09:58,660 --> 00:10:03,430
Is that just disgusting?
You have to concede it

73
00:10:03,530 --> 00:10:05,560
It's nothing but crusting

74
00:10:05,670 --> 00:10:11,260
Here, drink this, you'll need it
The worst pies in London

75
00:10:11,370 --> 00:10:13,900
And no wonder
with the price of meat what it is

76
00:10:14,010 --> 00:10:16,940
When you get it
Never thought I'd live to see the day

77
00:10:17,040 --> 00:10:20,140
Men'd think it was a treat
Finding poor animals

78
00:10:20,250 --> 00:10:21,370
What are dying in the street

79
00:10:21,480 --> 00:10:23,850
Mrs. Mooney has a pie shop

80
00:10:23,950 --> 00:10:26,480
Does her business
but I noticed something weird

81
00:10:26,590 --> 00:10:29,110
Lately all her neighbors' cats
have disappeared

82
00:10:29,220 --> 00:10:32,250
Have to hand it to her
What I calls enterprise

83
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:34,020
Popping pussies into pies

84
00:10:34,130 --> 00:10:36,290
Wouldn't do in my shop

85
00:10:36,400 --> 00:10:38,920
Just the thought of it's enough
to make you sick

86
00:10:39,030 --> 00:10:42,090
And I'm telling you
them pussycats is quick

87
00:10:42,200 --> 00:10:45,570
No denying times is hard, sir!

88
00:10:45,670 --> 00:10:49,610
Even harder than
the worst pies in London

89
00:10:49,710 --> 00:10:53,370
Only lard and nothing more
Is that just revolting

90
00:10:53,480 --> 00:10:55,450
All greasy and gritty

91
00:10:55,550 --> 00:10:57,740
It looks like it's molting

92
00:10:57,850 --> 00:10:59,840
And tastes like

93
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:01,350
Well, pity

94
00:11:01,460 --> 00:11:04,650
A woman alone!

95
00:11:05,560 --> 00:11:08,460
With limited wind

96
00:11:08,560 --> 00:11:13,560
And the worst pies in London

97
00:11:14,840 --> 00:11:16,100
Sir

98
00:11:16,740 --> 00:11:18,860
Times is hard

99
00:11:18,970 --> 00:11:24,610
Times is hard

100
00:11:27,080 --> 00:11:31,280
Trust me, dearie, it's gonna take a lot
more than ale to wash that taste out.

101
00:11:32,150 --> 00:11:35,590
Come with me.
We'll get you a nice tumbler of gin, eh?

102
00:11:48,340 --> 00:11:49,320
Isn't this homey, now?

103
00:11:51,010 --> 00:11:53,530
The cheery wallpaper
was a real bargain, too.

104
00:11:53,640 --> 00:11:56,240
It was only partly singed when
the chapel burned down.

105
00:11:56,340 --> 00:11:59,710
There you go.
You sit down, warm your bones.

106
00:12:00,350 --> 00:12:03,280
You've a room over the shop here?

107
00:12:03,380 --> 00:12:05,720
Times is so hard,
why don't you rent it out?

108
00:12:05,820 --> 00:12:08,790
What, up there? No, I won't go near it.

109
00:12:10,960 --> 00:12:13,020
People think it's haunted.

110
00:12:13,960 --> 00:12:15,830
- Haunted?
- Yeah.

111
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:19,460
And who's to say they're wrong?

112
00:12:20,170 --> 00:12:23,930
You see, years ago,
something happened up there.

113
00:12:24,040 --> 00:12:26,060
Something not very nice.

114
00:12:29,140 --> 00:12:31,910
There was a barber and his wife

115
00:12:33,110 --> 00:12:36,640
And he was beautiful

116
00:12:36,750 --> 00:12:40,120
A proper artist with a knife

117
00:12:40,220 --> 00:12:43,490
But they transported him for life

118
00:12:43,590 --> 00:12:47,030
And he was beautiful

119
00:12:48,730 --> 00:12:52,670
Barker, his name was. Benjamin Barker.

120
00:12:53,500 --> 00:12:55,700
What was his crime?

121
00:12:56,040 --> 00:12:57,630
Foolishness.

122
00:12:58,840 --> 00:13:01,470
He had this wife, you see

123
00:13:01,580 --> 00:13:03,740
Pretty little thing, silly little nit

124
00:13:03,840 --> 00:13:07,970
Had her chance
for the moon on a string

125
00:13:08,080 --> 00:13:10,410
Poor thing

126
00:13:11,820 --> 00:13:14,120
Poor thing

127
00:13:15,420 --> 00:13:17,910
There was this judge, you see

128
00:13:18,030 --> 00:13:22,590
Wanted her like mad
Every day he sent her a flower

129
00:13:22,700 --> 00:13:25,390
But did she come down from her tower?

130
00:13:26,170 --> 00:13:28,930
Sat up there and sobbed by the hour

131
00:13:29,470 --> 00:13:31,500
Poor fool

132
00:13:31,740 --> 00:13:34,970
But there was worse yet to come
poor thing

133
00:13:41,720 --> 00:13:46,380
Well, Beadle calls on her all polite
Poor thing

134
00:13:46,820 --> 00:13:48,450
Poor thing

135
00:13:48,560 --> 00:13:51,650
The Judge, he tells her is all contrite

136
00:13:51,760 --> 00:13:54,990
He blames himself
for her dreadful plight

137
00:13:55,100 --> 00:13:58,160
She must come straight
to his house tonight

138
00:13:58,270 --> 00:14:00,960
Poor thing, poor thing

139
00:14:06,140 --> 00:14:09,170
Of course, when she goes there
Poor thing, poor thing

140
00:14:09,280 --> 00:14:12,110
They're having this ball all in masks

141
00:14:12,210 --> 00:14:15,380
There's no one she knows there
Poor dear, poor thing

142
00:14:15,480 --> 00:14:18,450
She wanders tormented and drinks
Poor thing

143
00:14:18,550 --> 00:14:21,490
The Judge has repented, she thinks
Poor thing

144
00:14:21,590 --> 00:14:24,650
"Oh, where is Judge Turpin?"
She asks

145
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:29,330
He was there all right
Only not so contrite

146
00:14:31,970 --> 00:14:35,230
She wasn't no match for such craft
you see

147
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:38,030
And everyone thought it so droll

148
00:14:38,140 --> 00:14:41,010
They figured she had to be daft
you see

149
00:14:41,110 --> 00:14:44,100
So all of them stood there and laughed
you see

150
00:14:44,210 --> 00:14:45,510
Poor soul

151
00:14:46,950 --> 00:14:48,510
Poor thing...

152
00:14:56,490 --> 00:14:57,790
No!

153
00:15:00,090 --> 00:15:02,790
Would no one have mercy on her?

154
00:15:03,700 --> 00:15:05,630
So, it is you,

155
00:15:06,470 --> 00:15:08,160
Benjamin Barker?

156
00:15:09,800 --> 00:15:11,530
Where is Lucy?

157
00:15:13,070 --> 00:15:14,700
Where is my wife?

158
00:15:15,280 --> 00:15:17,240
She poisoned herself.

159
00:15:17,950 --> 00:15:21,040
Arsenic, from the apothecary
around the corner.

160
00:15:22,250 --> 00:15:25,620
Tried to stop her,
but she wouldn't listen to me.

161
00:15:29,190 --> 00:15:31,320
And he's got your daughter.

162
00:15:33,490 --> 00:15:34,830
He?

163
00:15:35,960 --> 00:15:37,560
Judge Turpin?

164
00:15:38,800 --> 00:15:42,030
Adopted her. Like his own.

165
00:15:43,970 --> 00:15:45,500
Fifteen years.

166
00:15:46,440 --> 00:15:49,810
I've sweated in a living hell
on a false charge.

167
00:15:51,880 --> 00:15:56,410
Fifteen years dreaming I might
come home to a wife and child.

168
00:15:58,090 --> 00:16:01,450
Well, I can't say the years have been
particularly kind to you, Mr. Barker.

169
00:16:01,560 --> 00:16:04,050
No. Not Barker.

170
00:16:05,290 --> 00:16:06,990
That man is dead.

171
00:16:08,100 --> 00:16:11,090
It's Todd now. Sweeney Todd.

172
00:16:12,870 --> 00:16:15,100
And he will have his revenge.

173
00:16:48,140 --> 00:16:49,730
Come in.

174
00:16:50,100 --> 00:16:52,440
Nothing to be afraid of, love.

175
00:17:39,320 --> 00:17:42,350
When they came for the girl, I hid them.

176
00:17:42,460 --> 00:17:45,080
Could've sold them, but I didn't.

177
00:17:56,940 --> 00:17:59,960
Those handles is chased silver,
ain't they?

178
00:18:01,740 --> 00:18:04,010
Silver. Yes.

179
00:18:13,990 --> 00:18:17,120
These are my friends

180
00:18:18,730 --> 00:18:22,820
See how they glisten

181
00:18:23,760 --> 00:18:27,060
See this one shine

182
00:18:27,700 --> 00:18:32,430
How he smiles in the light

183
00:18:32,540 --> 00:18:35,840
My friend

184
00:18:35,940 --> 00:18:40,140
My faithful friend

185
00:18:42,680 --> 00:18:46,550
Speak to me, friend

186
00:18:47,620 --> 00:18:51,150
Whisper, I'll listen

187
00:18:52,130 --> 00:18:55,560
I know, I know

188
00:18:55,660 --> 00:19:02,330
You've been locked
out of sight all these years

189
00:19:02,970 --> 00:19:07,170
Like me, my friend

190
00:19:07,270 --> 00:19:11,370
Well, I've come home

191
00:19:11,480 --> 00:19:15,640
To find you waiting

192
00:19:16,950 --> 00:19:19,420
Home

193
00:19:19,520 --> 00:19:23,510
And we're together

194
00:19:24,360 --> 00:19:28,090
And we'll do wonders

195
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,100
Won't we?

196
00:19:33,270 --> 00:19:36,030
You there, my friend

197
00:19:36,140 --> 00:19:40,040
- I'm your friend, too, Mr. Todd
- Come, let me hold you

198
00:19:40,140 --> 00:19:43,580
- lf you only knew, Mr. Todd
- Now, with a sigh

199
00:19:43,680 --> 00:19:44,910
Oh, Mr. Todd

200
00:19:45,010 --> 00:19:48,680
- you're warm in my hand
- You grow warm in my hand

201
00:19:48,780 --> 00:19:50,750
My friend

202
00:19:50,850 --> 00:19:54,580
- You've come home
- My clever friend

203
00:19:54,690 --> 00:19:58,450
Always had a fondness for you, I did

204
00:19:58,560 --> 00:20:01,260
Rest now, my friends

205
00:20:01,360 --> 00:20:05,630
- Never you fear, Mr. Todd
- Soon I'll unfold you

206
00:20:05,730 --> 00:20:08,460
- You can move in here, Mr. Todd
- Soon you'll know

207
00:20:08,570 --> 00:20:11,730
- Splendors you never
- Splendors you never

208
00:20:11,840 --> 00:20:15,000
- have dreamed all your days
- have dreamed all your days

209
00:20:15,110 --> 00:20:16,700
Will be yours

210
00:20:16,810 --> 00:20:19,370
My lucky friends

211
00:20:19,480 --> 00:20:23,540
- I'm your friend and now you're mine
- Till now your shine...

212
00:20:23,650 --> 00:20:27,920
- Don't they shine beautiful?
...was merely silver

213
00:20:28,020 --> 00:20:30,510
Silver's good enough for me

214
00:20:30,620 --> 00:20:36,490
- Friends, you shall drip rubies
- Mr. T

215
00:20:37,970 --> 00:20:41,490
You'll soon drip precious

216
00:20:43,300 --> 00:20:46,140
rubies

217
00:20:53,850 --> 00:20:55,340
Leave me.

218
00:21:08,800 --> 00:21:13,530
At last, my arm is complete again.

219
00:22:14,900 --> 00:22:19,200
Green finch and linnet bird
Nightingale, blackbird

220
00:22:19,300 --> 00:22:22,500
How is it you sing?

221
00:22:23,540 --> 00:22:27,600
How can you jubilate
Sitting in cages

222
00:22:27,710 --> 00:22:30,770
Never taking wing?

223
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:36,470
Outside the sky waits
Beckoning, beckoning

224
00:22:36,580 --> 00:22:39,310
Just beyond the bars

225
00:22:40,920 --> 00:22:44,080
How can you remain
Staring at the rain

226
00:22:44,190 --> 00:22:48,090
Maddened by the stars?

227
00:22:49,530 --> 00:22:53,730
How is it you sing anything?

228
00:22:54,430 --> 00:22:58,430
How is it you sing?

229
00:23:12,420 --> 00:23:16,480
My cage has many rooms
Damask and dark

230
00:23:16,590 --> 00:23:22,050
Nothing there sings
Not even my lark

231
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:26,570
Larks never will, you know
When they're captive

232
00:23:26,670 --> 00:23:31,930
Teach me to be more adaptive

233
00:23:37,110 --> 00:23:41,570
Green finch and linnet bird
Nightingale, blackbird

234
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:45,780
Teach me how to sing

235
00:23:45,890 --> 00:23:50,820
If I cannot fly

236
00:23:52,090 --> 00:23:58,730
Let me sing

237
00:24:10,140 --> 00:24:11,630
Alms!

238
00:24:11,780 --> 00:24:16,550
Alms for a miserable woman

239
00:24:18,390 --> 00:24:24,380
On a miserable chilly morning

240
00:24:26,530 --> 00:24:28,760
- Thank you, sir!
- Ma'am?

241
00:24:30,130 --> 00:24:32,890
Could you tell me whose house this is?

242
00:24:33,300 --> 00:24:36,290
That's the great
Judge Turpin's house, that is.

243
00:24:36,400 --> 00:24:38,770
And the young lady who resides there?

244
00:24:38,870 --> 00:24:42,870
Oh, that's Johanna,
his pretty little ward.

245
00:24:43,080 --> 00:24:46,410
Keeps her snug, he does. All locked up.

246
00:24:47,110 --> 00:24:51,850
So don't you go trespassing there,
or it's a good whipping for you,

247
00:24:51,950 --> 00:24:55,790
or any other young man
with mischief on his mind.

248
00:24:56,690 --> 00:24:58,160
Alms!

249
00:24:58,260 --> 00:25:03,320
Alms for a desperate woman

250
00:25:08,170 --> 00:25:12,260
I feel you

251
00:25:12,370 --> 00:25:16,310
Johanna

252
00:25:16,410 --> 00:25:20,740
I feel you

253
00:25:20,850 --> 00:25:24,750
I was half convinced I'd waken

254
00:25:24,850 --> 00:25:28,810
Satisfied enough to dream you

255
00:25:28,920 --> 00:25:35,020
Happily I was mistaken, Johanna

256
00:25:36,260 --> 00:25:40,260
I'll steal you

257
00:25:40,370 --> 00:25:44,170
Johanna!

258
00:25:44,270 --> 00:25:48,830
I'll steal you

259
00:26:03,420 --> 00:26:05,550
Come in, lad. Come in.

260
00:26:12,530 --> 00:26:14,970
You were looking for Hyde Park,
you say?

261
00:26:15,100 --> 00:26:16,360
Yes.

262
00:26:16,940 --> 00:26:20,430
It's very large on the map,
but I keep getting lost.

263
00:26:20,540 --> 00:26:22,600
Sit down, lad, sit down.

264
00:26:23,340 --> 00:26:28,010
It's embarrassing for a sailor
to lose his bearings, but there you are.

265
00:26:32,690 --> 00:26:34,150
A sailor?

266
00:26:35,620 --> 00:26:38,350
Yes, sir. The Bountiful, out of Plymouth.

267
00:26:38,490 --> 00:26:42,090
A sailor must know
the ways of the world, yes?

268
00:26:43,060 --> 00:26:46,520
Must be practiced
in the ways of the world.

269
00:26:46,630 --> 00:26:48,660
Would you say you were practiced, boy?

270
00:26:48,870 --> 00:26:52,130
- Sir?
- Oh, yes.

271
00:26:53,340 --> 00:26:56,670
Such practices.

272
00:26:58,350 --> 00:27:02,610
The geishas of Japan.
The concubines of Siam.

273
00:27:02,720 --> 00:27:07,180
The catamites of Greece.
The harlots of India.

274
00:27:08,790 --> 00:27:12,490
I have them all here. Drawings of them.

275
00:27:12,590 --> 00:27:18,120
Everything you've ever dreamed
of doing with a woman.

276
00:27:19,570 --> 00:27:21,430
Would you like to see?

277
00:27:22,540 --> 00:27:25,000
I think there's been some mistake.

278
00:27:25,870 --> 00:27:27,360
I think not.

279
00:27:29,610 --> 00:27:34,510
You gandered at my ward, Johanna.
You gandered at her.

280
00:27:34,610 --> 00:27:38,980
- Yes, sir, you gandered.
- I meant no harm.

281
00:27:39,090 --> 00:27:41,180
Your meaning is immaterial.

282
00:27:42,690 --> 00:27:44,160
Mark me.

283
00:27:44,260 --> 00:27:51,130
If I see your face again on this street,
you'll rue the day you were born.

284
00:27:55,300 --> 00:27:57,770
Hyde Park is that way, young sir!

285
00:27:57,870 --> 00:28:01,030
A left and a right and straight on,
you see?

286
00:28:01,140 --> 00:28:03,110
Move on, now!

287
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:15,150
You heard what Judge Turpin said,
little man.

288
00:28:15,890 --> 00:28:20,850
Next time, it'll be your pretty little brains
all over the pavement.

289
00:28:45,190 --> 00:28:49,020
I'll steal you

290
00:28:49,120 --> 00:28:53,080
Johanna

291
00:28:53,190 --> 00:28:57,460
I'll steal you

292
00:28:57,560 --> 00:29:01,400
Do they think that walls can hide you?

293
00:29:01,500 --> 00:29:05,370
Even now, I'm at your window

294
00:29:05,470 --> 00:29:10,000
I am in the dark beside you

295
00:29:10,110 --> 00:29:15,140
Buried sweetly in your yellow hair

296
00:29:22,020 --> 00:29:25,550
I feel you

297
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:29,490
Johanna

298
00:29:29,600 --> 00:29:33,460
And one day

299
00:29:33,570 --> 00:29:38,400
I'll steal you

300
00:29:38,510 --> 00:29:42,310
Till I'm with you then
I'm with you there!

301
00:29:42,410 --> 00:29:47,280
Sweetly buried in your yellow hair!

302
00:30:09,800 --> 00:30:13,330
He's here every Thursday.
Italian. All the rage he is.

303
00:30:14,210 --> 00:30:16,540
Best barber in London, they say.

304
00:30:48,010 --> 00:30:49,200
Hang on.

305
00:31:21,210 --> 00:31:25,340
Ladies and gentlemen
May I have your attention, please?

306
00:31:26,710 --> 00:31:28,680
Do you wake every morning
in shame and despair

307
00:31:28,780 --> 00:31:31,680
To discover your pillow
is covered with hair

308
00:31:31,780 --> 00:31:33,750
What ought not to be there?

309
00:31:33,850 --> 00:31:37,720
Well, ladies and gentlemen
From now on you can waken at ease

310
00:31:37,820 --> 00:31:39,690
You need never again
have a worry or care

311
00:31:39,790 --> 00:31:42,520
I will show you a miracle
marvelous rare

312
00:31:43,530 --> 00:31:45,330
Gentlemen, you are about
to see something

313
00:31:45,430 --> 00:31:48,330
What rose from the dead!

314
00:31:49,200 --> 00:31:51,230
On the top of my head!

315
00:31:53,740 --> 00:31:57,200
'Twas Pirelli's Miracle Elixir

316
00:31:57,310 --> 00:32:00,750
That's what did the trick, sir
True, sir, true

317
00:32:00,850 --> 00:32:04,370
Was it quick, sir? Did it in a tick, sir?

318
00:32:04,480 --> 00:32:08,080
Just like an elixir ought to do

319
00:32:08,190 --> 00:32:12,560
How about a bottle, mister?
Only costs a penny, guaranteed

320
00:32:15,230 --> 00:32:18,790
Does Pirelli's stimulate the growth, sir?

321
00:32:18,900 --> 00:32:22,230
You can have my oath, sir
'Tis unique

322
00:32:22,340 --> 00:32:25,790
Rub a minute
Stimulating, isn't it?

323
00:32:25,910 --> 00:32:29,640
Soon you'll have to thin it
Once a week!

324
00:32:29,740 --> 00:32:31,400
Pardon me, ma'am
what's that awful stench?

325
00:32:31,510 --> 00:32:33,140
Are we standing in an open trench?

326
00:32:33,250 --> 00:32:34,210
Must be standing near an open trench!

327
00:32:34,310 --> 00:32:35,300
Pardon me, sir
what's that awful stench?

328
00:32:35,420 --> 00:32:38,320
Buy Pirelli's Miracle Elixir

329
00:32:38,420 --> 00:32:41,980
Anything what's slick, sir
Soon sprouts curls

330
00:32:42,090 --> 00:32:45,490
Try Pirelli's
When they see how thick, sir

331
00:32:45,590 --> 00:32:49,190
You can have your pick, sir
Of the girls

332
00:32:49,300 --> 00:32:50,460
Want to buy a bottle, missus?

333
00:32:50,560 --> 00:32:52,090
- What is this?
- What is this?

334
00:32:52,200 --> 00:32:54,720
- Smells like piss
- Smells like...

335
00:32:54,830 --> 00:32:56,630
- Looks like piss!
- Wouldn't touch it if I was you, dear!

336
00:32:56,740 --> 00:33:00,170
- This is piss, piss with ink
- Let Pirelli's activate your roots, sir!

337
00:33:00,270 --> 00:33:01,800
Keep it off your boots, sir
Eats right through

338
00:33:01,910 --> 00:33:04,740
Yes, get Pirelli's, use a bottle of it
Ladies seem to love it

339
00:33:04,840 --> 00:33:06,740
Flies do, too

340
00:33:09,580 --> 00:33:11,450
I am Adolfo Pirelli

341
00:33:11,550 --> 00:33:13,610
The king of the barbers
The barber of kings

342
00:33:13,720 --> 00:33:16,990
E buon giorno, good day!
I blow you a kiss!

343
00:33:17,590 --> 00:33:19,420
And I

344
00:33:19,530 --> 00:33:21,720
the so famous Pirelli
I wish-a to know-a

345
00:33:21,830 --> 00:33:24,700
Who has-a the nerve-a to say

346
00:33:24,800 --> 00:33:26,960
My elixir is piss

347
00:33:27,930 --> 00:33:30,130
Who says this?

348
00:33:32,670 --> 00:33:33,900
I do.

349
00:33:36,010 --> 00:33:38,770
I am Mr. Sweeney Todd of Fleet Street.

350
00:33:39,980 --> 00:33:42,350
I have opened a bottle of Pirelli's Elixir.

351
00:33:42,450 --> 00:33:46,410
And I say to you that it is nothing
but an arrant fraud,

352
00:33:47,350 --> 00:33:50,150
concocted from piss and ink.

353
00:33:51,190 --> 00:33:54,960
Furthermore, Signor,
I have serviced no kings,

354
00:33:56,160 --> 00:34:00,930
yet I wager that I can shave a cheek
with 10 times more dexterity,

355
00:34:01,030 --> 00:34:03,370
than any street mountebank.

356
00:34:08,310 --> 00:34:10,280
Do you see these razors?

357
00:34:11,180 --> 00:34:13,740
I lay them against (pound)5.

358
00:34:14,580 --> 00:34:16,570
You are no match, sir.

359
00:34:17,280 --> 00:34:21,980
Either accept my challenge,
or reveal yourself as a sham.

360
00:34:24,020 --> 00:34:26,120
You hear this foolish man?

361
00:34:26,790 --> 00:34:32,130
Now, please, you will see
how he will-a regret-a his-a folly.

362
00:34:33,130 --> 00:34:34,600
Toby!

363
00:34:34,700 --> 00:34:36,630
Who's for a free shave?

364
00:34:59,460 --> 00:35:01,590
Will Beadle Bamford be the judge?

365
00:35:01,730 --> 00:35:06,390
Glad, as always,
to oblige my friends and neighbors.

366
00:35:17,880 --> 00:35:19,070
Ready?

367
00:35:19,750 --> 00:35:20,970
Ready!

368
00:35:21,580 --> 00:35:22,840
Ready.

369
00:35:23,480 --> 00:35:27,940
The fastest,
smoothest shave is the winner!

370
00:35:52,680 --> 00:35:55,370
Now, signorini, signori
We mix-a the lather

371
00:35:55,480 --> 00:35:58,380
But first-a
You gather around, signorini, signori

372
00:35:58,480 --> 00:36:01,510
You looking a man who have
had-a the glory to shave-a the Pope!

373
00:36:01,620 --> 00:36:03,820
Mr. Sweeney, whoever
I beg-a you pardon

374
00:36:03,920 --> 00:36:06,320
You'll probably say
it was only a cardinal

375
00:36:06,430 --> 00:36:07,790
Nope!

376
00:36:07,890 --> 00:36:09,730
It was-a the Pope!

377
00:36:12,100 --> 00:36:16,930
To shave-a the face
To cut-a the hair

378
00:36:17,040 --> 00:36:22,060
Require the grace
Require the flair

379
00:36:22,180 --> 00:36:24,670
For if-a you slip
You nick the skin

380
00:36:24,780 --> 00:36:27,370
You clip-a the chin
You rip-a the lip a bit

381
00:36:27,480 --> 00:36:29,780
Beyond-a repair

382
00:36:30,380 --> 00:36:32,510
To shave-a the face

383
00:36:33,320 --> 00:36:37,090
Or even a part
Without it-a smart

384
00:36:37,820 --> 00:36:40,690
Require the heart

385
00:36:40,790 --> 00:36:43,280
Not just-a the flash

386
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:48,930
It take-a panache
It take-a the passion for the art

387
00:36:50,840 --> 00:36:55,300
To shave-a the face
To trim-a the beard

388
00:36:55,940 --> 00:37:00,170
To make-a the bristle
Clean like a whistle

389
00:37:00,280 --> 00:37:06,220
This is from early infancy
The talent give to me

390
00:37:06,490 --> 00:37:09,510
By God

391
00:37:12,730 --> 00:37:16,720
It take-a the skill
It take-a the brains

392
00:37:17,230 --> 00:37:22,900
It take-a da will
To take-a the pains

393
00:37:23,670 --> 00:37:28,830
It take-a the pace
It take-a the grace

394
00:37:37,980 --> 00:37:40,780
The winner is Todd!

395
00:37:52,300 --> 00:37:56,200
Sir, I bow to a skill
far greater than my own.

396
00:37:57,570 --> 00:37:59,130
The (pound)5.

397
00:38:05,610 --> 00:38:08,080
May the good Lord smile on you.

398
00:38:09,580 --> 00:38:11,450
Until we meet again.

399
00:38:12,220 --> 00:38:14,120
Come, boy. Come!

400
00:38:23,630 --> 00:38:25,260
Suppose it's just me gentle heart,

401
00:38:25,360 --> 00:38:28,460
but I do hate to see a boy
treated like that.

402
00:38:28,570 --> 00:38:31,040
Congratulations, Mr. Todd.

403
00:38:31,140 --> 00:38:33,970
May I ask you, sir,
do you have your own establishment?

404
00:38:34,070 --> 00:38:35,630
He certainly does.

405
00:38:35,740 --> 00:38:38,070
Sweeney Todd's Tonsorial Parlor,

406
00:38:38,180 --> 00:38:41,240
above my Meat Pie Emporium
in Fleet Street.

407
00:38:44,920 --> 00:38:46,980
I thank you, sir.

408
00:38:47,090 --> 00:38:49,850
You are a paragon of integrity.

409
00:38:49,960 --> 00:38:54,120
Well, I try to do my best for
my friends and neighbors.

410
00:38:54,960 --> 00:38:58,360
Your establishment
is in Fleet Street, you say?

411
00:38:58,630 --> 00:39:01,070
- Yes, sir.
- Then, Mr. Todd,

412
00:39:01,570 --> 00:39:05,630
you shall surely see me there
before the week is out.

413
00:39:05,940 --> 00:39:08,430
You will be welcome, Beadle Bamford.

414
00:39:08,540 --> 00:39:12,770
And I can guarantee to give you,
without a penny's charge,

415
00:39:12,880 --> 00:39:15,510
the closest shave you will ever know.

416
00:39:26,130 --> 00:39:27,750
Come on, love.

417
00:40:47,410 --> 00:40:49,700
It's not much of a chair, but it'll do.

418
00:40:49,810 --> 00:40:52,970
It was me poor Albert's chair.
Sit in it all day long he did,

419
00:40:53,080 --> 00:40:55,340
after his leg gave out with the gout.

420
00:40:55,450 --> 00:40:57,380
Why doesn't the Beadle come?

421
00:40:57,480 --> 00:41:00,680
"Before the week is out,"
that's what he said.

422
00:41:00,790 --> 00:41:04,090
Well, who says the week's out?
It's only Tuesday.

423
00:41:08,190 --> 00:41:12,860
Easy now
Hush, love, hush

424
00:41:12,970 --> 00:41:17,270
Don't distress yourself
What's your rush?

425
00:41:17,370 --> 00:41:21,600
Keep your thoughts
Nice and lush

426
00:41:21,710 --> 00:41:23,300
Wait

427
00:41:26,180 --> 00:41:30,440
Hush, love, hush
Think it through

428
00:41:30,550 --> 00:41:34,580
Once it bubbles
Then what's to do?

429
00:41:34,690 --> 00:41:38,890
Watch it close
Let it brew

430
00:41:38,990 --> 00:41:40,250
Wait

431
00:41:42,090 --> 00:41:46,790
I've been thinking flowers
Maybe daisies

432
00:41:46,900 --> 00:41:48,960
To brighten up the room

433
00:41:50,340 --> 00:41:55,140
Don't you think some flowers
Pretty daisies

434
00:41:55,240 --> 00:41:57,770
Might relieve the gloom?

435
00:41:59,580 --> 00:42:00,880
Wait

436
00:42:02,750 --> 00:42:05,180
Love, wait

437
00:42:05,280 --> 00:42:08,050
And the Judge? When'll we get to him?

438
00:42:09,190 --> 00:42:12,360
Can't you think of nothing else?
Always brooding away on your wrongs

439
00:42:12,360 --> 00:42:12,650
Can't you think of nothing else?
Always brooding away on your wrongs

440
00:42:12,760 --> 00:42:15,690
and what happened
heaven knows how many years ago.

441
00:42:15,790 --> 00:42:17,280
Come on.

442
00:42:17,400 --> 00:42:21,130
Slow, love, slow
Time's so fast

443
00:42:21,730 --> 00:42:26,000
Now goes quickly
See, now it's past

444
00:42:26,110 --> 00:42:30,060
Soon will come
Soon will last

445
00:42:30,180 --> 00:42:31,540
Wait

446
00:42:34,610 --> 00:42:38,710
Don't you know
Silly man

447
00:42:38,820 --> 00:42:42,340
Half the fun is to plan the plan?

448
00:42:43,060 --> 00:42:47,120
All good things
come to those who can

449
00:42:47,230 --> 00:42:48,450
Wait

450
00:42:51,660 --> 00:42:56,330
Gillyflowers, maybe
'Stead of daisies

451
00:42:56,540 --> 00:43:01,000
I don't know, though
What do you think?

452
00:43:10,920 --> 00:43:12,580
Oh, I'm sorry, excuse me.

453
00:43:12,690 --> 00:43:15,350
- Mrs. Lovett, sir.
- A pleasure, ma'am.

454
00:43:16,220 --> 00:43:18,280
Mr. Todd,
there's a girl who needs my help.

455
00:43:18,390 --> 00:43:20,420
Such a sad girl and Ionely,
but beautiful, too and...

456
00:43:20,530 --> 00:43:24,090
- Slow down, son.
- Yes. I'm sorry.

457
00:43:25,530 --> 00:43:27,470
This girl has a guardian
who keeps her locked away,

458
00:43:27,570 --> 00:43:29,630
but then, this morning,
she dropped this.

459
00:43:29,740 --> 00:43:32,000
Surely a sign
that Johanna wants me to help her.

460
00:43:32,100 --> 00:43:33,660
That's her name, Johanna.

461
00:43:33,770 --> 00:43:37,000
And Turpin is her guardian.
He's a judge of some sort.

462
00:43:37,110 --> 00:43:39,040
Once he goes to court,
I'm going to slip into the house,

463
00:43:39,140 --> 00:43:41,510
release her and beg her
to come away with me tonight.

464
00:43:41,610 --> 00:43:44,010
- Oh, this is very romantic.
- Yes.

465
00:43:45,050 --> 00:43:47,110
But I don't know anyone in London,
you see.

466
00:43:47,220 --> 00:43:51,210
And I need somewhere safe to bring her
till I've hired a coach to take us away.

467
00:43:51,320 --> 00:43:53,350
If I could keep her here
just for an hour or two,

468
00:43:53,460 --> 00:43:55,690
I'd be forever in your debt.

469
00:43:59,470 --> 00:44:02,900
- Bring her here, love.
- Thank you, ma'am.

470
00:44:03,870 --> 00:44:05,230
Mr. Todd?

471
00:44:07,140 --> 00:44:09,330
Oh, thank you.
Thank you, thank you, my friend.

472
00:44:09,440 --> 00:44:11,140
Thank you, ma'am.

473
00:44:14,250 --> 00:44:17,740
Seems like the Fates
are favoring you at last, Mr. T.

474
00:44:19,180 --> 00:44:22,680
What is it? You'll have her back
before the day is out.

475
00:44:23,460 --> 00:44:24,750
What about him?

476
00:44:25,720 --> 00:44:26,880
Him?

477
00:44:26,990 --> 00:44:29,590
Oh, well. Let him bring her here.

478
00:44:29,700 --> 00:44:32,600
And then, since you're so hot for a little,

479
00:44:33,830 --> 00:44:36,360
that's the throat to slit, my dear.

480
00:44:38,140 --> 00:44:39,900
Poor little Johanna.

481
00:44:40,010 --> 00:44:43,440
All those years without a scrap
of motherly affection.

482
00:44:43,940 --> 00:44:47,040
Well, I'll soon see to that.

483
00:44:55,250 --> 00:44:58,550
Hello. What's he doing here?

484
00:45:00,560 --> 00:45:02,820
Keep the boy downstairs.

485
00:45:14,140 --> 00:45:16,570
Signora, is Mr. Todd at home?

486
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:18,800
Plying his trade upstairs.

487
00:45:19,880 --> 00:45:21,540
Would you look at it now?

488
00:45:21,650 --> 00:45:24,140
You wouldn't mind if I gave it a nice
juicy meat pie, would you?

489
00:45:24,250 --> 00:45:28,050
- Si, si, si. Whatever you want.
- Come on, lad.

490
00:45:28,520 --> 00:45:30,920
Your teeth are strong, I hope.

491
00:45:32,460 --> 00:45:36,020
Close the door.
Get you a nice lovely pie.

492
00:45:38,860 --> 00:45:41,200
Sit down. Make yourself comfy.

493
00:45:48,670 --> 00:45:50,110
Come in.

494
00:45:58,980 --> 00:46:01,680
- Mr. Todd.
- Signor Pirelli.

495
00:46:03,290 --> 00:46:04,780
Call me Davey.

496
00:46:05,820 --> 00:46:09,190
Davey Collin's the name
when it's not professional.

497
00:46:10,430 --> 00:46:12,860
I'd like me five quid back,
if you don't mind.

498
00:46:12,970 --> 00:46:14,060
Why?

499
00:46:14,170 --> 00:46:18,190
Because you entered into our little
wager under false pretenses, my friend.

500
00:46:18,300 --> 00:46:22,930
So that you might remember
to be a bit more forthright in the future,

501
00:46:23,040 --> 00:46:24,980
I'll be taking half your profits
from herewith.

502
00:46:25,080 --> 00:46:27,010
Share and share alike.

503
00:46:28,550 --> 00:46:30,950
Mr. Benjamin Barker.

504
00:46:33,490 --> 00:46:36,550
Here we are. Tuck in.

505
00:46:40,160 --> 00:46:43,090
I like to see a man
with a healthy appetite.

506
00:46:43,200 --> 00:46:45,490
Reminds me of my dear Albert.

507
00:46:46,100 --> 00:46:49,690
Liked to gorge himself
to bloatation, he did.

508
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:52,100
He didn't have
your nice head of hair, though.

509
00:46:52,200 --> 00:46:55,440
To tell the truth, it gets awful hot.

510
00:46:59,610 --> 00:47:01,770
Yes, this'll do nicely.

511
00:47:05,420 --> 00:47:08,750
You don't remember me, do you?
Why should you?

512
00:47:08,850 --> 00:47:11,190
I was just a little nip
that you hired for a couple of weeks,

513
00:47:11,290 --> 00:47:13,260
sweeping up hair.

514
00:47:14,190 --> 00:47:16,250
But I remember these.

515
00:47:17,100 --> 00:47:20,120
And how could
I ever forget you, Mr. Barker.

516
00:47:24,440 --> 00:47:26,600
I used to sit right here.

517
00:47:27,540 --> 00:47:30,410
Dream of the day
when I could be a proper barber myself.

518
00:47:30,510 --> 00:47:34,240
You might say that you was
inspiration to me.

519
00:47:46,590 --> 00:47:48,460
So, is we got a deal?

520
00:47:49,860 --> 00:47:53,890
Or should I run down the street
to me old pal, Beadle Bamford?

521
00:47:57,500 --> 00:48:01,700
What do you say to that, now,
Mr. Sweeney Todd?

522
00:48:24,360 --> 00:48:27,390
My, my, my. Always work to be done.

523
00:48:27,500 --> 00:48:29,830
Spic and span, that's my motto.

524
00:48:42,510 --> 00:48:45,880
So, how'd you end up
with that dreadful Italian?

525
00:48:45,980 --> 00:48:50,350
Got me from the workhouse.
Been there since I was born.

526
00:48:50,460 --> 00:48:53,050
Oh, God!
He's got an appointment with his tailor!

527
00:48:53,160 --> 00:48:54,750
If he's late, he'll blame me!

528
00:48:54,860 --> 00:48:56,120
Wait!

529
00:49:02,770 --> 00:49:05,290
Signor! You got an appointment!

530
00:49:10,540 --> 00:49:14,340
Signor Pirelli's been called away.
Better run after him.

531
00:49:15,310 --> 00:49:19,750
No, sir. I should stay here,
or it'll be a lashing.

532
00:49:19,850 --> 00:49:22,550
He's a great one for the lashings.

533
00:49:28,430 --> 00:49:29,590
So,

534
00:49:30,900 --> 00:49:34,830
- Mrs. Lovett gave you a pie, did she?
- She's a real lady.

535
00:49:35,700 --> 00:49:37,330
That she is.

536
00:49:42,210 --> 00:49:47,200
But if I know a growing boy,
there's still room for more pie, eh?

537
00:49:47,310 --> 00:49:48,610
Yes, sir.

538
00:49:49,880 --> 00:49:52,680
Then why don't you wait
for your master downstairs?

539
00:49:52,780 --> 00:49:57,150
- Be another pie in it for you, I'm sure.
- No, I should stay here.

540
00:49:59,890 --> 00:50:03,830
Tell you what,
why don't you tell Mrs. Lovett

541
00:50:03,930 --> 00:50:07,390
that I said to give you
a nice big tot of gin.

542
00:50:07,500 --> 00:50:09,060
Thank you, sir!

543
00:51:17,070 --> 00:51:19,370
This is the second time, sir,

544
00:51:19,470 --> 00:51:22,600
you have been brought
before this bench.

545
00:51:23,840 --> 00:51:27,940
Though it is my earnest wish ever
to temper justice with mercy,

546
00:51:28,050 --> 00:51:31,210
your persistent dedication
to a life of crime

547
00:51:31,320 --> 00:51:34,980
is an abomination before God and man.

548
00:51:35,090 --> 00:51:38,550
I therefore sentence you
to hang by the neck until you're dead.

549
00:51:38,660 --> 00:51:41,630
And may the Lord
have mercy on your soul.

550
00:51:42,690 --> 00:51:44,460
Court is adjourned.

551
00:51:53,440 --> 00:51:55,930
Thank you, Your Honor.

552
00:51:56,040 --> 00:51:59,480
- Just the sentence we wanted.
- Was he guilty?

553
00:51:59,580 --> 00:52:00,700
Well, if he didn't do it,

554
00:52:00,810 --> 00:52:03,250
he's surely done
something to warrant a hanging.

555
00:52:03,350 --> 00:52:06,040
- What man has not?
- Sorry?

556
00:52:09,050 --> 00:52:10,820
No matter. Come.

557
00:52:12,020 --> 00:52:13,680
Walk home with me.

558
00:52:16,730 --> 00:52:19,420
I have news for you, my friend.

559
00:52:19,530 --> 00:52:22,560
In order to shield her
from the evils of this world,

560
00:52:22,670 --> 00:52:26,000
I have decided to marry
my dear Johanna.

561
00:52:26,100 --> 00:52:28,500
Sir, happy news indeed.

562
00:52:28,610 --> 00:52:30,170
Strange though,

563
00:52:30,780 --> 00:52:36,440
when I offered myself to her,
she showed a certain reluctance.

564
00:52:37,350 --> 00:52:40,050
Excuse me, my lord
May I request, my lord

565
00:52:40,150 --> 00:52:42,550
Permission, my lord, to speak?

566
00:52:42,650 --> 00:52:44,920
Forgive me if I suggest, my lord

567
00:52:45,020 --> 00:52:47,390
You're looking less
than your best, my lord

568
00:52:47,490 --> 00:52:52,190
There's powder upon your vest, my lord
And stubble upon your cheek

569
00:52:55,330 --> 00:52:59,240
And ladies, my lord, are weak

570
00:53:00,040 --> 00:53:02,300
Stubble, you say?

571
00:53:05,640 --> 00:53:09,100
Perhaps I am
a little overhasty in the mornings.

572
00:53:10,220 --> 00:53:12,680
Fret not though, my lord
I know a place, my lord

573
00:53:12,780 --> 00:53:15,310
A barber, my lord, of skill

574
00:53:15,420 --> 00:53:17,620
Thus armed with a shaven face, my lord

575
00:53:17,720 --> 00:53:20,020
Some eau de cologne to grace, my lord

576
00:53:20,130 --> 00:53:22,590
And musk to enhance the chase
my lord

577
00:53:22,690 --> 00:53:25,560
You'll dazzle the girl until

578
00:53:26,460 --> 00:53:27,830
Until?

579
00:53:28,400 --> 00:53:32,600
She bows to your every will

580
00:53:33,670 --> 00:53:34,970
Barber?

581
00:53:36,270 --> 00:53:37,300
Take me to him.

582
00:53:37,410 --> 00:53:42,110
His name is Todd, my lord, and he is
the very last word in barbering.

583
00:53:48,790 --> 00:53:52,220
You ought to slow down a bit, lad.
It'll go straight to your head.

584
00:53:52,320 --> 00:53:53,920
They used to give it to us
in the workhouse

585
00:53:54,030 --> 00:53:55,790
so as we could sleep.

586
00:53:55,890 --> 00:53:58,060
Not that you'd want
to sleep in that place, ma'am.

587
00:53:58,160 --> 00:54:00,530
Not with the things
what happen in the dark.

588
00:54:00,630 --> 00:54:01,960
That's nice, dear.

589
00:54:02,070 --> 00:54:03,900
Think I'll just pop in
on Mr. Todd for a tick.

590
00:54:04,000 --> 00:54:06,840
- You all right, there?
- Leave the bottle.

591
00:54:11,840 --> 00:54:15,240
That lad is drinking me
out of house and home.

592
00:54:16,250 --> 00:54:18,580
How long till Pirelli gets back?

593
00:54:19,220 --> 00:54:20,950
He won't be back.

594
00:54:22,820 --> 00:54:24,690
Mr. T, you didn't.

595
00:54:35,900 --> 00:54:39,500
You're barking mad.
Killing a man what done you no harm.

596
00:54:40,340 --> 00:54:44,270
He recognized me from the old days.
Tried to blackmail me.

597
00:54:45,540 --> 00:54:47,170
Half me earnings.

598
00:54:47,880 --> 00:54:50,680
Oh, well, it's a different matter then.

599
00:54:51,580 --> 00:54:55,080
For a moment there,
I thought you'd lost your marbles.

600
00:54:58,160 --> 00:54:59,780
All that blood.

601
00:55:01,290 --> 00:55:02,760
Poor bugger.

602
00:55:03,630 --> 00:55:04,990
Oh, well.

603
00:55:13,410 --> 00:55:15,810
Well, waste not, want not.

604
00:55:17,440 --> 00:55:20,710
So, what are we gonna do
about the boy then?

605
00:55:22,210 --> 00:55:23,740
Send him up.

606
00:55:24,680 --> 00:55:27,650
Oh, we don't need to worry about him.
He's a simple thing.

607
00:55:27,750 --> 00:55:29,280
Send him up!

608
00:55:32,190 --> 00:55:35,650
Now, Mr. T,
surely one's enough for today.

609
00:55:36,800 --> 00:55:40,290
Besides, I was thinking of hiring the lad
to help me run the shop.

610
00:55:40,400 --> 00:55:43,370
Your poor knees
aren't what they used to be.

611
00:55:44,170 --> 00:55:45,600
All right.

612
00:55:47,640 --> 00:55:49,940
Course, we're gonna
have to stock up on the gin.

613
00:55:50,040 --> 00:55:52,070
Boy drinks like a sailor.

614
00:55:56,210 --> 00:55:57,510
The Judge.

615
00:56:01,020 --> 00:56:02,280
Get out.

616
00:56:04,360 --> 00:56:05,620
Get out!

617
00:56:22,010 --> 00:56:23,500
Mr. Todd?

618
00:56:24,540 --> 00:56:26,170
At your service.

619
00:56:27,350 --> 00:56:30,470
An honor to receive
your patronage, my lord.

620
00:56:31,750 --> 00:56:33,450
You know me, sir?

621
00:56:33,850 --> 00:56:39,090
Who in this wide world
does not know the great Judge Turpin?

622
00:56:45,700 --> 00:56:47,600
These premises
are hardly prepossessing,

623
00:56:47,700 --> 00:56:49,530
and yet the Beadle tells me

624
00:56:49,630 --> 00:56:53,540
you're the most accomplished
of all the barbers in the city.

625
00:56:54,210 --> 00:56:56,570
That is gracious of him, sir.

626
00:56:57,640 --> 00:57:00,080
What may I do for you today, sir?

627
00:57:00,850 --> 00:57:03,640
A stylish trimming of the hair?

628
00:57:03,750 --> 00:57:05,740
Soothing skin massage?

629
00:57:05,850 --> 00:57:07,580
Sit, sir. Sit.

630
00:57:08,750 --> 00:57:13,710
You see, sir, a man infatuate with love
Her ardent and eager slave

631
00:57:13,830 --> 00:57:18,730
So fetch the pomade and pumice stone
And lend me a more seductive tone

632
00:57:18,830 --> 00:57:23,270
A sprinkling perhaps of French cologne
But first, sir, I think

633
00:57:24,340 --> 00:57:26,930
a shave

634
00:57:28,710 --> 00:57:31,800
The closest I ever gave

635
00:57:36,450 --> 00:57:38,750
You're in a merry mood today, Mr. Todd.

636
00:57:38,850 --> 00:57:44,020
'Tis your delight, sir, catching fire
From one man to the next

637
00:57:44,120 --> 00:57:46,680
'Tis true, sir, love can still inspire

638
00:57:46,790 --> 00:57:49,190
The blood to pound
the heart leap higher

639
00:57:49,290 --> 00:57:50,660
- What more
- What more

640
00:57:50,760 --> 00:57:52,920
- can man require than love, sir
- can man require

641
00:57:53,920 --> 00:57:55,120
More than love, sir

642
00:57:55,220 --> 00:57:56,520
- What, sir?
- Women

643
00:57:56,620 --> 00:57:59,060
- Yes, women
- Pretty women

644
00:58:30,260 --> 00:58:34,420
Now then, my friend

645
00:58:35,530 --> 00:58:39,400
Now to your purpose

646
00:58:40,400 --> 00:58:44,130
Patience, enjoy it

647
00:58:45,010 --> 00:58:49,440
Revenge can't be taken in haste

648
00:58:49,540 --> 00:58:51,740
Make haste, and if we wed
You'll be commended, sir

649
00:58:51,850 --> 00:58:53,210
My lord

650
00:58:55,820 --> 00:58:58,250
And who, may it be said
Is your intended, sir?

651
00:58:58,350 --> 00:59:00,840
My ward

652
00:59:02,090 --> 00:59:04,420
A pretty little rosebud.

653
00:59:04,530 --> 00:59:06,430
Pretty as her mother?

654
00:59:07,460 --> 00:59:10,060
What? What was that?

655
00:59:10,160 --> 00:59:14,460
Nothing, sir. Nothing. May we proceed?

656
00:59:16,200 --> 00:59:17,800
Pretty women

657
00:59:18,410 --> 00:59:22,770
Fascinating
Sipping coffee

658
00:59:23,640 --> 00:59:28,780
Dancing
Pretty women!

659
00:59:28,880 --> 00:59:31,250
Are a wonder

660
00:59:31,350 --> 00:59:33,820
Pretty women

661
00:59:36,620 --> 00:59:41,490
Sitting in the window or

662
00:59:41,600 --> 00:59:46,500
Standing on the stair

663
00:59:46,600 --> 00:59:53,200
Something in them
Cheers the air

664
00:59:56,880 --> 00:59:58,670
Pretty women

665
00:59:59,680 --> 01:00:01,510
Silhouetted

666
01:00:02,150 --> 01:00:04,550
Stay within you

667
01:00:04,650 --> 01:00:07,180
Glancing!

668
01:00:07,290 --> 01:00:09,550
Stay forever

669
01:00:09,660 --> 01:00:12,280
Breathing lightly

670
01:00:12,390 --> 01:00:14,490
Pretty women

671
01:00:14,600 --> 01:00:17,000
- Pretty women
- Pretty women

672
01:00:17,100 --> 01:00:21,860
- Blowing out their candles or
- Blowing out their candles or

673
01:00:21,970 --> 01:00:25,230
- Combing out their hair
- Combing out their hair

674
01:00:25,340 --> 01:00:26,860
Then they leave

675
01:00:26,970 --> 01:00:28,870
- Even when they leave...
- Even when they

676
01:00:28,980 --> 01:00:30,500
leave you and vanish...

677
01:00:30,610 --> 01:00:33,510
...they still...
...they somehow can still remain...

678
01:00:33,610 --> 01:00:39,080
...are there, they're there
...there with you

679
01:00:39,190 --> 01:00:40,210
- Pretty women
- Pretty women

680
01:00:40,320 --> 01:00:41,840
- At their mirrors
- In their gardens

681
01:00:41,960 --> 01:00:43,480
- Letter-writing
- Flower-picking

682
01:00:43,590 --> 01:00:44,610
weather-watching

683
01:00:44,730 --> 01:00:49,530
- How they make a man sing
- How they make a man sing

684
01:00:49,630 --> 01:00:52,160
- Proof of heaven
- Proof of heaven

685
01:00:52,270 --> 01:00:54,600
- As you're living
- As you're living

686
01:00:54,700 --> 01:00:57,100
- Pretty women, sir!
- Pretty women, sir!

687
01:00:57,200 --> 01:00:59,300
- Pretty women, yes!
- Pretty women, yes!

688
01:00:59,410 --> 01:01:02,810
- Pretty women, sir
- Pretty women, pretty women

689
01:01:02,910 --> 01:01:04,500
Mr. Todd! I've seen Johanna

690
01:01:04,610 --> 01:01:07,340
and she said
she'd leave with me tonight.

691
01:01:09,620 --> 01:01:11,020
You.

692
01:01:11,120 --> 01:01:15,320
There is indeed a higher power
to warn me thus in time.

693
01:01:15,420 --> 01:01:17,320
Johanna elope with you?

694
01:01:19,090 --> 01:01:20,220
I'll make sure that neither you

695
01:01:20,330 --> 01:01:23,630
nor any other man
shall ever set eyes on her again.

696
01:01:24,330 --> 01:01:25,800
As for you, barber,

697
01:01:25,900 --> 01:01:28,330
it's all too clear
what company you keep.

698
01:01:28,440 --> 01:01:30,530
Service them well
and hold their custom,

699
01:01:30,640 --> 01:01:32,430
for you'll have none of mine.

700
01:01:32,540 --> 01:01:34,770
- Mr. Todd. You have to help me.
- Out.

701
01:01:34,880 --> 01:01:36,270
- Mr. Todd, please.
- Out.

702
01:01:36,380 --> 01:01:38,310
- Mr. Todd!
- Out!

703
01:01:43,980 --> 01:01:45,280
All this shouting and running about.

704
01:01:45,390 --> 01:01:47,550
- What's happened?
- I had him.

705
01:01:47,650 --> 01:01:48,850
The sailor busted in, I know.

706
01:01:48,960 --> 01:01:50,390
And then I saw them both
running down the stairs.

707
01:01:50,490 --> 01:01:51,960
I had him!

708
01:01:52,060 --> 01:01:54,120
His throat was bare beneath my hand

709
01:01:54,230 --> 01:01:57,130
- There, there, dear. Calm down.
- No, I had him!

710
01:01:57,230 --> 01:01:59,660
His throat was there
And he'll never come again!

711
01:01:59,770 --> 01:02:02,700
Easy now. Hush, love, hush

712
01:02:02,800 --> 01:02:04,830
- I'll keep telling you
- When?

713
01:02:04,940 --> 01:02:07,030
- What's your rush?
- Why did I wait?

714
01:02:07,140 --> 01:02:11,040
You told me to wait!
Now he'll never come again!

715
01:02:13,580 --> 01:02:15,480
There's a hole in the world
like a great black pit

716
01:02:15,580 --> 01:02:17,480
And it's filled with people
who are filled with shit

717
01:02:17,580 --> 01:02:20,750
And the vermin of the world inhabit it

718
01:02:20,850 --> 01:02:23,380
But not for long!

719
01:02:26,490 --> 01:02:30,730
They all deserve to die

720
01:02:30,830 --> 01:02:35,230
Tell you why, Mrs. Lovett
Tell you why

721
01:02:35,340 --> 01:02:38,100
Because in all of
the whole human race, Mrs. Lovett

722
01:02:38,210 --> 01:02:40,540
There are two kinds of men
and only two

723
01:02:40,640 --> 01:02:42,730
There's the one staying put
In his proper place

724
01:02:42,840 --> 01:02:45,140
And the one with his foot
In the other one's face

725
01:02:45,250 --> 01:02:47,410
Look at me, Mrs. Lovett, look at you!

726
01:02:47,510 --> 01:02:51,850
No, we all deserve to die

727
01:02:51,950 --> 01:02:56,390
Even you, Mrs. Lovett
Even I

728
01:02:56,490 --> 01:02:59,220
Because the lives of the wicked
should be made brief

729
01:02:59,330 --> 01:03:01,520
For the rest of us, death will be a relief

730
01:03:01,630 --> 01:03:05,930
We all deserve to die

731
01:03:06,030 --> 01:03:12,170
And I'll never see Johanna

732
01:03:12,270 --> 01:03:18,400
No, I'll never hug my girl to me

733
01:03:18,510 --> 01:03:20,240
Finished!

734
01:03:21,620 --> 01:03:25,310
All right! You, sir. How about a shave?

735
01:03:25,420 --> 01:03:29,190
Come and visit
your good friend Sweeney.

736
01:03:29,290 --> 01:03:32,120
You, sir, too, sir.
Welcome to the grave!

737
01:03:32,230 --> 01:03:36,220
I will have vengeance

738
01:03:36,330 --> 01:03:41,460
I will have salvation

739
01:03:43,400 --> 01:03:44,390
Who, sir?

740
01:03:44,500 --> 01:03:47,170
You, sir? No one's in the chair.
Come on, come on.

741
01:03:47,270 --> 01:03:50,840
Sweeney's waiting! I want you bleeders.

742
01:03:50,940 --> 01:03:54,240
You, sir! Anybody!
Gentlemen, now don't be shy!

743
01:03:54,350 --> 01:04:00,010
Not one man, no, nor ten men

744
01:04:00,120 --> 01:04:06,550
Nor a hundred can assuage me

745
01:04:06,660 --> 01:04:10,560
I will have you

746
01:04:11,130 --> 01:04:14,660
And I will get him back
Even as he gloats

747
01:04:14,770 --> 01:04:18,070
In the meantime
I'll practice on less honorable throats

748
01:04:18,170 --> 01:04:24,440
And my Lucy lies in ashes

749
01:04:24,540 --> 01:04:31,180
And I'll never see my girl again

750
01:04:31,280 --> 01:04:34,780
But the work waits!

751
01:04:35,990 --> 01:04:38,920
I'm alive at last!

752
01:04:39,460 --> 01:04:45,560
And I'm full of joy!

753
01:04:52,240 --> 01:04:54,000
That's all very well,
but what are we gonna do about him?

754
01:04:59,580 --> 01:05:00,840
Hello?

755
01:05:04,410 --> 01:05:05,970
Do you hear me?

756
01:05:09,080 --> 01:05:10,570
Come on.

757
01:05:11,350 --> 01:05:13,550
You great useless thing.

758
01:05:19,860 --> 01:05:21,300
Sit down.

759
01:05:41,280 --> 01:05:43,150
There. Drink it down.

760
01:05:45,250 --> 01:05:48,850
Now, we got a body
moldering away upstairs.

761
01:05:48,960 --> 01:05:51,860
Now, what do you intend
we should do about that, then?

762
01:05:51,960 --> 01:05:54,220
Later on when it's dark,

763
01:05:54,330 --> 01:05:57,630
we'll take it to some secret place
and bury it.

764
01:05:57,730 --> 01:06:00,330
Oh, yeah. Course we could do that.

765
01:06:03,510 --> 01:06:04,970
Don't suppose he's got any relatives

766
01:06:05,070 --> 01:06:06,940
that's gonna come poking around
looking for him.

767
01:06:12,310 --> 01:06:15,040
Seems a downright shame

768
01:06:15,380 --> 01:06:16,650
Shame?

769
01:06:18,290 --> 01:06:20,520
Seems an awful waste

770
01:06:22,620 --> 01:06:26,560
Such a nice plump frame
What's his name has

771
01:06:26,660 --> 01:06:28,990
Had, has

772
01:06:29,500 --> 01:06:32,230
Nor it can't be traced

773
01:06:33,340 --> 01:06:35,930
Business needs a lift

774
01:06:36,740 --> 01:06:39,230
Debts to be erased

775
01:06:40,080 --> 01:06:43,270
Think of it as thrift, as a gift

776
01:06:43,980 --> 01:06:46,070
If you get my drift.

777
01:06:46,720 --> 01:06:50,120
Seems an awful waste

778
01:06:52,390 --> 01:06:55,520
I mean, with the price of meat what it is

779
01:06:55,790 --> 01:06:58,890
When you get it, if you get it

780
01:06:59,460 --> 01:07:00,590
Good, you got it

781
01:07:00,700 --> 01:07:04,660
Take, for instance
Mrs. Mooney and her pie shop

782
01:07:04,770 --> 01:07:08,860
Business never better
using only pussycats and toast

783
01:07:08,970 --> 01:07:12,840
Now a pussy's good for
maybe six or seven at the most

784
01:07:12,940 --> 01:07:14,840
And I'm sure they can't
compare as far as taste

785
01:07:14,940 --> 01:07:17,500
Mrs. Lovett, what a charming notion
Eminently practical

786
01:07:17,610 --> 01:07:19,910
- And yet appropriate as always
- Well, it does seem a waste

787
01:07:20,020 --> 01:07:22,780
Mrs. Lovett, how I've lived without you
All these years I'll never know!

788
01:07:22,880 --> 01:07:23,870
Think about it

789
01:07:23,990 --> 01:07:25,010
- Iots of other gentlemen'll...
- How delectable!

790
01:07:25,120 --> 01:07:26,450
...soon be coming for a shave
- Also undetectable

791
01:07:26,560 --> 01:07:29,350
- Won't they? Think of all them pies!
- How choice! How rare!

792
01:07:29,460 --> 01:07:33,050
For what's the sound
of the world out there?

793
01:07:33,160 --> 01:07:36,100
What, Mr. Todd, what, Mr. Todd
What is that sound?

794
01:07:36,200 --> 01:07:39,730
Those crunching
noises pervading the air?

795
01:07:39,840 --> 01:07:42,740
Yes, Mr. Todd
Yes, Mr. Todd, yes, all around

796
01:07:42,840 --> 01:07:46,100
It's man devouring man, my dear

797
01:07:46,210 --> 01:07:50,740
- And who are we to deny it in here?
- And who are we to deny it in here?

798
01:07:54,120 --> 01:07:57,020
These are desperate times, Mrs. Lovett.

799
01:07:57,720 --> 01:08:00,650
And desperate measures are called for.

800
01:08:00,920 --> 01:08:04,290
Here we are, hot out of the oven.

801
01:08:05,360 --> 01:08:06,550
What is that?

802
01:08:06,660 --> 01:08:09,690
It's priest
Have a little priest

803
01:08:09,800 --> 01:08:13,200
- Is it really good?
- Sir, it's too good, at least

804
01:08:13,300 --> 01:08:16,570
Then again
they don't commit sins of the flesh

805
01:08:16,670 --> 01:08:18,540
So it's pretty fresh

806
01:08:20,210 --> 01:08:21,840
Awful lot of fat

807
01:08:21,940 --> 01:08:23,380
Only where it sat

808
01:08:23,480 --> 01:08:27,040
Haven't you got poet
or something like that?

809
01:08:27,150 --> 01:08:31,950
No, you see the trouble with poet is
how do you know it's deceased?

810
01:08:32,050 --> 01:08:34,080
Try the priest

811
01:08:43,070 --> 01:08:44,930
Lawyer's rather nice.

812
01:08:45,030 --> 01:08:46,830
If it's for a price

813
01:08:46,940 --> 01:08:51,840
Order something else, though, to follow
Since no one should swallow it twice

814
01:08:51,940 --> 01:08:53,640
Anything that's lean?

815
01:08:53,740 --> 01:08:58,610
Well, then, if you're British and loyal
You might enjoy Royal Marine

816
01:08:58,710 --> 01:09:00,440
Anyway, it's clean

817
01:09:00,550 --> 01:09:03,710
Though, of course
it tastes of wherever it's been

818
01:09:03,820 --> 01:09:07,220
Is that squire on the fire?

819
01:09:07,320 --> 01:09:10,760
Mercy no, sir, look closer
You'll notice it's grocer

820
01:09:10,860 --> 01:09:13,850
Looks thicker
More like vicar

821
01:09:13,960 --> 01:09:17,260
No, it has to be grocer
It's green

822
01:09:20,770 --> 01:09:24,500
The history of the world, my love

823
01:09:24,610 --> 01:09:27,270
Save a lot of graves
Do a lot of relatives favors

824
01:09:27,380 --> 01:09:31,340
Is those below serving those up above

825
01:09:31,450 --> 01:09:34,010
Everybody shaves
So there should be plenty of flavors

826
01:09:34,120 --> 01:09:37,240
How gratifying for once to know

827
01:09:37,350 --> 01:09:38,790
- That those above
- That those above

828
01:09:38,890 --> 01:09:42,850
- will serve those down below!
- Will serve those down below!

829
01:09:49,130 --> 01:09:50,160
What is that?

830
01:09:50,270 --> 01:09:53,670
It's fop
Finest in the shop

831
01:09:53,770 --> 01:09:58,470
Or we have some shepherd's pie
peppered with actual shepherd on top

832
01:09:58,570 --> 01:10:00,340
And I've just begun

833
01:10:00,440 --> 01:10:05,350
Here's the politician, so oily
It's served with a doily, have one

834
01:10:05,450 --> 01:10:07,140
Put it on a bun

835
01:10:07,250 --> 01:10:10,650
Well, you never know if it's going to run

836
01:10:10,750 --> 01:10:13,880
Try the friar, fried, it's drier

837
01:10:13,990 --> 01:10:17,760
No, the clergy is really
Too coarse and too mealy

838
01:10:17,860 --> 01:10:20,990
Then actor
It's compacter

839
01:10:21,100 --> 01:10:24,030
But always arrives overdone

840
01:10:24,130 --> 01:10:27,500
I'll come again
when you have judge on the menu.

841
01:10:33,910 --> 01:10:37,440
Have charity towards the world, my pet

842
01:10:37,550 --> 01:10:40,480
Yes, yes, I know, my love

843
01:10:40,580 --> 01:10:44,180
We'll take the customers
that we can get

844
01:10:44,290 --> 01:10:46,910
High-born and low, my love

845
01:10:47,020 --> 01:10:50,010
We'll not discriminate great from small

846
01:10:50,130 --> 01:10:52,220
No, we'll serve anyone

847
01:10:52,330 --> 01:10:53,850
- We'll serve anyone
- Meaning anyone

848
01:10:53,960 --> 01:10:58,090
- And to anyone at all!
- And to anyone at all!

849
01:11:17,550 --> 01:11:19,020
So, it's true.

850
01:11:19,960 --> 01:11:24,620
Sir, a gentleman knocks
before entering a lady's room.

851
01:11:24,860 --> 01:11:27,520
Indeed he does, but I see no lady.

852
01:11:30,400 --> 01:11:32,920
I told myself the sailor was lying,

853
01:11:33,030 --> 01:11:37,400
that my Johanna would never betray me,
never hurt me so.

854
01:11:37,510 --> 01:11:40,270
Sir, I will leave this place.

855
01:11:41,440 --> 01:11:44,170
I think that only appropriate

856
01:11:44,280 --> 01:11:48,480
since you no longer find
my company to your liking.

857
01:11:51,020 --> 01:11:53,950
We shall provide you with new lodgings.

858
01:11:56,790 --> 01:12:00,590
Until this moment I have spared the rod.

859
01:12:01,860 --> 01:12:05,560
But the ungrateful child
has broken my heart.

860
01:12:07,170 --> 01:12:09,100
When you've learned
to appreciate what you have,

861
01:12:09,200 --> 01:12:10,900
perhaps we shall meet again.

862
01:12:11,010 --> 01:12:12,560
Until then

863
01:12:14,110 --> 01:12:16,980
think on your sins.

864
01:12:24,190 --> 01:12:25,380
No!

865
01:12:29,490 --> 01:12:31,020
No, please!

866
01:12:34,400 --> 01:12:37,560
Johanna! Where are you taking her?
Tell me or I swear I'II...

867
01:12:37,670 --> 01:12:40,190
You'd kill me, boy? Here I stand!

868
01:12:42,040 --> 01:12:43,530
Johanna!

869
01:13:50,040 --> 01:13:54,370
I feel you

870
01:13:54,480 --> 01:13:58,310
Johanna

871
01:13:58,410 --> 01:14:02,280
I feel you

872
01:14:02,920 --> 01:14:06,510
Do they think that walls can hide you?

873
01:14:06,620 --> 01:14:10,460
Even now, I'm at your window

874
01:14:10,560 --> 01:14:15,000
I am in the dark beside you

875
01:14:15,100 --> 01:14:20,230
Buried sweetly in your yellow hair

876
01:14:20,340 --> 01:14:24,830
Johanna

877
01:14:32,850 --> 01:14:36,410
And are you beautiful and pale

878
01:14:36,520 --> 01:14:39,610
With yellow hair, like her?

879
01:14:39,720 --> 01:14:43,180
I'd want you beautiful and pale

880
01:14:43,290 --> 01:14:49,530
The way I've dreamed you were
Johanna

881
01:14:52,970 --> 01:14:59,370
And if you're beautiful
what then with yellow hair, like wheat

882
01:14:59,470 --> 01:15:03,040
I think we shall not meet again

883
01:15:03,140 --> 01:15:06,110
My little dove, my sweet Johanna

884
01:15:06,210 --> 01:15:12,550
I'll steal you, Johanna!

885
01:15:12,650 --> 01:15:14,990
Goodbye, Johanna!

886
01:15:16,020 --> 01:15:19,120
You're gone, and yet you're mine

887
01:15:19,230 --> 01:15:21,560
I'm fine, Johanna

888
01:15:21,660 --> 01:15:28,360
- I'm fine!
- Johanna

889
01:15:35,180 --> 01:15:41,550
Smoke! Smoke! Sign of the devil
Sign of the devil. City on fire!

890
01:15:41,650 --> 01:15:44,740
Witch! Witch! Smell it, sir
An evil smell

891
01:15:44,850 --> 01:15:46,550
Every night at the vespers bell

892
01:15:46,650 --> 01:15:48,280
Smoke that comes from
the mouth of hell

893
01:15:48,390 --> 01:15:51,360
City on fire!

894
01:15:51,460 --> 01:15:54,660
City on fire

895
01:15:55,460 --> 01:15:58,020
Mischief! Mischief! Mischief!

896
01:16:06,470 --> 01:16:12,940
And if I never hear your voice
My turtledove, my dear

897
01:16:13,050 --> 01:16:18,710
I still have reason to rejoice
The way ahead is clear

898
01:16:18,820 --> 01:16:23,020
Johanna

899
01:16:24,830 --> 01:16:25,820
I feel

900
01:16:25,930 --> 01:16:31,490
And in that darkness when I'm blind
With what I can't forget

901
01:16:31,600 --> 01:16:32,620
Johanna

902
01:16:32,730 --> 01:16:35,760
It's always morning in my mind

903
01:16:35,870 --> 01:16:42,140
My little lamb, my pet, Johanna

904
01:16:45,150 --> 01:16:48,310
- You stay, Johanna...
- Johanna

905
01:16:48,420 --> 01:16:51,150
...the way I've dreamed you are

906
01:16:51,650 --> 01:16:55,250
Oh, look, Johanna! A star!

907
01:16:55,360 --> 01:16:59,920
Buried sweetly in your yellow hair

908
01:17:00,030 --> 01:17:03,430
A shooting star!

909
01:17:07,340 --> 01:17:11,270
There, there, somebody, somebody
look up there. Didn't I tell you?

910
01:17:11,370 --> 01:17:15,270
Smell that air. City on fire!

911
01:17:15,380 --> 01:17:18,280
Quick, sir, run and tell
Warn them all of the witch's spell

912
01:17:18,380 --> 01:17:20,010
There it is, there it is, the unholy smell

913
01:17:20,110 --> 01:17:22,310
Tell it to the Beadle and police as well
Tell them! Tell them

914
01:17:22,420 --> 01:17:26,250
Help, fiend! City on fire!

915
01:17:26,350 --> 01:17:29,760
City on fire

916
01:17:29,860 --> 01:17:31,620
Mischief. Mischief.

917
01:17:41,470 --> 01:17:47,900
And though I'll think of you, I guess
Until the day I die

918
01:17:48,010 --> 01:17:53,710
I think I miss you less and less
As every day goes by

919
01:17:53,820 --> 01:18:00,550
- Johanna
- Johanna

920
01:18:00,660 --> 01:18:06,990
And you'd be beautiful and pale
And look too much like her

921
01:18:07,100 --> 01:18:12,800
If only angels could prevail
We'd be the way we were

922
01:18:12,900 --> 01:18:19,770
- Johanna
- I feel you, Johanna

923
01:18:19,870 --> 01:18:22,900
Wake up, Johanna

924
01:18:23,010 --> 01:18:26,110
Another bright red day

925
01:18:26,210 --> 01:18:32,920
We learn, Johanna, to say

926
01:18:34,590 --> 01:18:36,080
Goodbye

927
01:18:39,760 --> 01:18:43,320
I'll steal

928
01:18:46,400 --> 01:18:51,270
you

929
01:19:28,740 --> 01:19:32,510
Ladies and gentlemen
May I have your attention, please?

930
01:19:34,080 --> 01:19:36,070
Are your nostrils a-quiver
and tingling as well

931
01:19:36,180 --> 01:19:39,240
At that delicate
luscious ambrosial smell?

932
01:19:39,350 --> 01:19:41,450
Yes, they are, I can tell

933
01:19:41,560 --> 01:19:45,390
Well, ladies and gentlemen
That aroma enriching the breeze

934
01:19:45,490 --> 01:19:47,430
Is like nothing
compared to its succulent source

935
01:19:47,530 --> 01:19:51,190
As the gourmets among you
will tell you, of course

936
01:19:51,300 --> 01:19:56,130
Ladies and gentlemen
You can't imagine the rapture in store

937
01:19:57,170 --> 01:19:59,470
Just inside of this door!

938
01:20:03,750 --> 01:20:07,200
There you'll sample
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies

939
01:20:07,320 --> 01:20:10,770
Savory and sweet pies
As you'll see

940
01:20:10,890 --> 01:20:14,340
You who eat pies
Mrs. Lovett's meat pies

941
01:20:14,460 --> 01:20:17,950
Conjure up the treat
pies used to be!

942
01:20:21,700 --> 01:20:23,430
- Toby!
- Coming!

943
01:20:24,500 --> 01:20:26,230
- Ale there!
- Right, ma'am!

944
01:20:26,330 --> 01:20:27,730
Quick, now!

945
01:20:28,970 --> 01:20:32,600
Nice to see you, dearie
How have you been keeping?

946
01:20:32,710 --> 01:20:36,300
Cor, me bones is weary
Toby! One for the gentleman

947
01:20:36,410 --> 01:20:39,970
Hear the birdies cheeping
Helps to keep it cheery

948
01:20:40,080 --> 01:20:43,520
Toby! Throw the old woman out!

949
01:20:43,620 --> 01:20:47,420
What's my secret?
Frankly, dear, forgive my candor

950
01:20:47,520 --> 01:20:50,980
Family secret
All to do with herbs

951
01:20:51,090 --> 01:20:54,550
Things like being
careful with your coriander

952
01:20:54,660 --> 01:20:57,100
That's what makes the gravy grander!

953
01:20:57,100 --> 01:20:57,390
That's what makes the gravy grander!

954
01:21:07,240 --> 01:21:10,770
Eat them slow and feel the crust
How thin she rolled it

955
01:21:10,880 --> 01:21:14,510
Eat them slow
'cause every one's a prize!

956
01:21:14,620 --> 01:21:18,050
Eat them slow 'cause that's the lot
and now we've sold it!

957
01:21:18,150 --> 01:21:19,410
Come again tomorrow!

958
01:21:19,520 --> 01:21:20,820
Hold it!

959
01:21:21,820 --> 01:21:23,880
Bless my eyes!

960
01:21:25,530 --> 01:21:27,460
Fresh supplies!

961
01:21:27,560 --> 01:21:28,930
- How about it, dearie?
- Is that a pie...

962
01:21:29,030 --> 01:21:30,830
- Be here in a twinkling!
...fit for a king

963
01:21:30,930 --> 01:21:33,560
- Just confirms me theory, Toby!
- A wondrous sweet

964
01:21:33,670 --> 01:21:34,830
- and most delectable thing?
- God watches over us

965
01:21:34,940 --> 01:21:36,630
Didn't have an inkling, positively eerie

966
01:21:36,740 --> 01:21:38,030
You see, ma'am
why there's no meat pie

967
01:21:38,140 --> 01:21:40,800
Toby! Throw the old woman out!

968
01:21:48,880 --> 01:21:52,150
Still got to keep an eye
on the household expenditure.

969
01:21:53,790 --> 01:21:56,420
Which isn't to say we couldn't get
some nice taxidermy animals,

970
01:21:56,520 --> 01:21:58,820
bring a touch of gentility to the place.

971
01:21:58,930 --> 01:22:01,420
You know, a boar's head or two?

972
01:22:02,630 --> 01:22:06,400
- Mr. T? You listening to me?
- Of course.

973
01:22:07,000 --> 01:22:12,060
- Then what did I just say?
- There must be a way to the Judge.

974
01:22:12,170 --> 01:22:15,300
Judge. Always harping
on the bloody old judge.

975
01:22:16,340 --> 01:22:18,570
We got a nice
respectable business now.

976
01:22:18,680 --> 01:22:20,540
Money coming in regular-like.

977
01:22:20,650 --> 01:22:22,340
And since we're careful
to pick and choose,

978
01:22:22,450 --> 01:22:26,610
strangers, people who won't be missed,
who's gonna catch on?

979
01:22:28,260 --> 01:22:30,380
Mr. Todd, I'm so happy

980
01:22:30,490 --> 01:22:32,620
I could eat you up, I really could

981
01:22:32,730 --> 01:22:35,960
You know what I'd like to do, Mr. Todd?
What I dream?

982
01:22:36,060 --> 01:22:39,760
If the business stays as good
Where I'd really like to go

983
01:22:40,370 --> 01:22:44,700
In a year or so?
Don't you want to know?

984
01:22:44,810 --> 01:22:45,930
Of course.

985
01:22:46,040 --> 01:22:47,870
Do you really want to know?

986
01:22:47,980 --> 01:22:49,880
Yes, I do.

987
01:23:04,630 --> 01:23:07,590
By the sea, Mr. Todd
That's the life I'll covet

988
01:23:07,700 --> 01:23:10,560
By the sea, Mr. Todd
Oh, I know you'd love it

989
01:23:10,670 --> 01:23:15,690
You and me, Mr. T, we could be alone
In a house what we'd almost own

990
01:23:15,800 --> 01:23:19,030
- Down by the sea
- Anything you say

991
01:23:19,140 --> 01:23:21,940
Wouldn't that be smashing?

992
01:23:22,840 --> 01:23:25,970
Think how snug it'll be
Underneath our flannel

993
01:23:26,080 --> 01:23:29,050
When it's just you and me
And the English Channel

994
01:23:29,150 --> 01:23:31,950
In our cozy retreat
Kept all neat and tidy

995
01:23:32,050 --> 01:23:37,220
We'll have chums over every Friday
By the sea

996
01:23:37,330 --> 01:23:42,820
Don't you love the weather
by the sea?

997
01:23:43,700 --> 01:23:46,790
We'll grow old together

998
01:23:47,100 --> 01:23:51,560
By the seaside
By the beautiful sea

999
01:23:56,680 --> 01:23:59,670
lt'll be so quiet that who'll come by it

1000
01:23:59,780 --> 01:24:02,110
except a seagull?

1001
01:24:02,980 --> 01:24:07,420
We shouldn't try it
though, till it's legal for two!

1002
01:24:08,790 --> 01:24:11,920
But a seaside wedding could be devised

1003
01:24:12,030 --> 01:24:14,860
Me rumpled bedding legitimized

1004
01:24:14,960 --> 01:24:20,590
Me eyelids'll flutter, I'll turn into butter
The moment I mutter "I do!"

1005
01:24:20,700 --> 01:24:24,360
Will you take this woman
to be your lawfully wedded wife?

1006
01:24:28,510 --> 01:24:30,530
You may kiss your bride.

1007
01:24:42,920 --> 01:24:48,790
Down by the sea
Married nice and proper

1008
01:24:49,000 --> 01:24:54,590
By the sea
Bring along your chopper

1009
01:24:54,700 --> 01:25:01,160
To the seaside
By the beautiful sea

1010
01:25:19,390 --> 01:25:22,020
I brought you some breakfast, dear.

1011
01:25:25,900 --> 01:25:28,930
Mr. T? Can I ask you a question?

1012
01:25:30,140 --> 01:25:31,230
What?

1013
01:25:32,310 --> 01:25:34,600
What did your Lucy look like?

1014
01:25:37,550 --> 01:25:39,810
Can't really remember, can you?

1015
01:25:41,150 --> 01:25:43,120
She had yellow hair.

1016
01:25:45,050 --> 01:25:47,950
You gotta leave this all behind,
you know.

1017
01:25:49,760 --> 01:25:51,350
She's gone.

1018
01:25:52,990 --> 01:25:55,290
Life is for the alive, my dear.

1019
01:25:56,430 --> 01:25:59,160
We could have a life, us two.

1020
01:25:59,270 --> 01:26:01,290
Maybe not like I dreamed.

1021
01:26:02,370 --> 01:26:04,530
Maybe not like you remember.

1022
01:26:05,610 --> 01:26:07,400
But we could get by.

1023
01:26:16,020 --> 01:26:20,150
- Mr. Todd! Mrs. Lovett, ma'am?
- What is it, Anthony?

1024
01:26:20,250 --> 01:26:24,120
- He has her locked in a madhouse.
- Johanna.

1025
01:26:24,230 --> 01:26:25,690
Fogg's Asylum.

1026
01:26:25,790 --> 01:26:30,560
I've circled the place a dozen times.
There's no way in. It's a fortress.

1027
01:26:30,660 --> 01:26:33,570
- I've got him.
- Mr. Todd?

1028
01:26:34,840 --> 01:26:36,460
We've got her.

1029
01:26:37,810 --> 01:26:39,170
Where do you suppose
all the wigmakers

1030
01:26:39,270 --> 01:26:41,710
in London go to obtain their hair?

1031
01:26:42,510 --> 01:26:43,740
Bedlam.

1032
01:26:44,550 --> 01:26:48,410
- They get it from the lunatics at Bedlam.
- I don't understand.

1033
01:26:49,920 --> 01:26:52,940
We shall set you up
as a wigmaker's apprentice.

1034
01:26:53,050 --> 01:26:56,180
That'll gain you access.
And then you take her.

1035
01:26:56,920 --> 01:26:58,590
Go, quickly, go!

1036
01:27:00,090 --> 01:27:01,530
Fetch the boy.

1037
01:27:01,630 --> 01:27:04,960
Don't you think you should
leave the boy behind?

1038
01:27:19,510 --> 01:27:23,610
- Toby. Mr. Todd needs you.
- Yes, ma'am.

1039
01:27:36,600 --> 01:27:37,930
Mr. T?

1040
01:27:40,500 --> 01:27:44,460
- Do you know where the Old Bailey is?
- Yes, sir. Not that I ever been there.

1041
01:27:44,570 --> 01:27:48,670
Take this there.
Seek out a Judge Turpin. Repeat that.

1042
01:27:48,780 --> 01:27:51,240
Go to Old Bailey. Find Judge Turpin.

1043
01:27:51,350 --> 01:27:54,780
You put that into his hands.
Only to him, you understand?

1044
01:27:54,880 --> 01:27:55,970
Yes, sir.

1045
01:27:56,080 --> 01:27:58,350
And while I'm out, do you mind
if I stop by the grocer just to pick...

1046
01:27:58,450 --> 01:28:01,110
No. You're not to stop,
you're not to speak.

1047
01:28:01,220 --> 01:28:03,820
You're to deliver the letter.
Do you understand?

1048
01:28:03,920 --> 01:28:05,450
Yes, sir.

1049
01:28:35,620 --> 01:28:37,090
Where you been, lad?

1050
01:28:37,190 --> 01:28:41,860
We had quite the rush at dinner time.
Me poor bones is ready to drop.

1051
01:28:41,960 --> 01:28:44,260
Mr. Todd sent me on an errand.

1052
01:28:44,370 --> 01:28:45,350
And on the way back,

1053
01:28:45,470 --> 01:28:48,330
I went by the workhouse,
just to take a look.

1054
01:28:48,440 --> 01:28:52,240
And I was thinking, but for you,
I'd be there now.

1055
01:28:53,340 --> 01:28:55,140
Or someplace worse.

1056
01:28:55,240 --> 01:28:57,230
Seems like the good Lord
sent you for me.

1057
01:28:57,340 --> 01:29:00,710
Oh, love, I feel quite the same way.

1058
01:29:00,810 --> 01:29:02,710
Listen to me, please.

1059
01:29:02,820 --> 01:29:05,080
You know there's nothing
I wouldn't do for you.

1060
01:29:05,190 --> 01:29:08,310
Say, if there were someone around,

1061
01:29:09,220 --> 01:29:10,990
someone bad?

1062
01:29:11,590 --> 01:29:13,990
Only you didn't know it.

1063
01:29:14,090 --> 01:29:17,830
What is this?
What are you talking about?

1064
01:29:19,970 --> 01:29:26,430
Nothing's gonna harm you
Not while I'm around

1065
01:29:27,910 --> 01:29:33,400
Nothing's gonna harm you
No, sir, not while I'm around

1066
01:29:33,510 --> 01:29:35,040
What do you mean "someone bad"?

1067
01:29:35,150 --> 01:29:41,680
Demons are prowling everywhere
nowadays

1068
01:29:42,520 --> 01:29:48,790
I'll send them howling, I don't care
I got ways

1069
01:29:50,060 --> 01:29:53,000
Hush, darling, there's no need for this.

1070
01:29:54,740 --> 01:30:01,110
No one's gonna hurt you
No one's gonna dare

1071
01:30:02,380 --> 01:30:08,010
Others can desert you
Not to worry, whistle, I'll be there

1072
01:30:08,850 --> 01:30:12,620
Demons will charm you
With a smile

1073
01:30:12,720 --> 01:30:18,520
For a while, but in time

1074
01:30:18,630 --> 01:30:21,390
Nothing can harm you

1075
01:30:22,630 --> 01:30:27,760
Not while I'm around

1076
01:30:31,370 --> 01:30:33,030
That's nice, dear.

1077
01:30:33,740 --> 01:30:38,370
Now, what is all this foolishness?
What are you talking about?

1078
01:30:39,110 --> 01:30:42,980
Little things that
I've been thinking about Mr. Todd.

1079
01:30:43,950 --> 01:30:48,950
Not to worry, not to worry
I may not be smart, but I ain't dumb

1080
01:30:50,220 --> 01:30:55,420
I can do it, put me to it
Show me something I can overcome

1081
01:30:56,700 --> 01:31:00,720
Not to worry, ma'am

1082
01:31:03,540 --> 01:31:08,030
Being close and being clever
Ain't like being true

1083
01:31:09,110 --> 01:31:14,640
I don't need to, I won't never
Hide a thing from you

1084
01:31:14,750 --> 01:31:18,150
Like some

1085
01:31:19,920 --> 01:31:24,120
Now, Toby, dear, haven't we
had enough of this foolish chatter?

1086
01:31:24,220 --> 01:31:25,560
Here.

1087
01:31:25,660 --> 01:31:30,820
How about I give you
a nice shiny new penny

1088
01:31:30,930 --> 01:31:33,660
and you go get us some toffees?

1089
01:31:36,000 --> 01:31:37,660
That's Signor Pirelli's purse!

1090
01:31:37,770 --> 01:31:40,600
No, it's not. Just something Mr. T
gave me for my birthday.

1091
01:31:40,710 --> 01:31:42,610
That proves it! We gotta go, ma'am.

1092
01:31:42,710 --> 01:31:44,840
We gotta find the Beadle
and get the law here!

1093
01:31:44,980 --> 01:31:47,810
Toby. Hush, lad,
you're not going anywhere.

1094
01:31:47,920 --> 01:31:52,910
You just sit here, nice and quiet,
next to me. That's right, right.

1095
01:31:55,820 --> 01:31:58,490
How could you think
such a thing of Mr. Todd?

1096
01:31:58,590 --> 01:32:01,120
He's been so good to us.

1097
01:32:05,330 --> 01:32:11,860
Nothing's gonna harm you
Not while I'm around

1098
01:32:13,670 --> 01:32:19,170
Nothing's gonna harm you, darling
Not while I'm around

1099
01:32:20,450 --> 01:32:26,110
Demons'll charm you with a smile
For a while

1100
01:32:26,220 --> 01:32:29,350
But in time

1101
01:32:29,460 --> 01:32:33,450
Nothing's gonna harm you

1102
01:32:33,560 --> 01:32:39,190
Not while I'm around

1103
01:32:42,970 --> 01:32:45,940
Funny we should be having
this little chat right now.

1104
01:32:46,040 --> 01:32:48,230
'Cause I was just thinking...

1105
01:32:49,140 --> 01:32:51,770
You know how you've always fancied
coming into the bake house with me

1106
01:32:51,880 --> 01:32:55,010
- to help make the pies?
- Yes, ma'am.

1107
01:32:55,180 --> 01:32:59,520
Well, no time like the present, eh?

1108
01:33:19,410 --> 01:33:22,840
I feel bad for you, going up
and down all these stairs.

1109
01:33:22,940 --> 01:33:26,740
- Well, that'll be your job now.
- Yes, ma'am.

1110
01:33:31,190 --> 01:33:33,450
Quite a stink, ain't there?

1111
01:33:37,160 --> 01:33:38,490
You see those grates?

1112
01:33:38,590 --> 01:33:41,390
They go right down to the sewers,
and the smells come up.

1113
01:33:41,500 --> 01:33:43,900
Always a few rats gone home
to Jesus down there.

1114
01:33:44,000 --> 01:33:47,900
Now, this'll be the bake oven.
Three dozen at a time.

1115
01:33:48,000 --> 01:33:50,770
Always be sure
the door is closed properly, like this.

1116
01:33:50,870 --> 01:33:54,470
- Door's closed properly.
- This is a grinder.

1117
01:33:55,080 --> 01:33:58,410
Pop in the meat. Give it a good grind.

1118
01:34:01,720 --> 01:34:03,410
Pops out there.

1119
01:34:05,320 --> 01:34:06,680
You try.

1120
01:34:08,390 --> 01:34:09,620
Good grind.

1121
01:34:11,260 --> 01:34:12,990
Comes out there.

1122
01:34:15,000 --> 01:34:16,330
That's my boy.

1123
01:34:16,430 --> 01:34:19,260
I'm just gonna pop upstairs,
back in two shakes, all right?

1124
01:34:19,370 --> 01:34:22,600
You mind if I have a pie while I wait?

1125
01:34:22,700 --> 01:34:24,690
As many as you like, son.

1126
01:34:37,520 --> 01:34:38,880
Yes, sir, I agree.

1127
01:34:38,990 --> 01:34:40,450
It would be to our mutual interest

1128
01:34:40,550 --> 01:34:44,490
to come to some arrangement
in regard to my poor children's hair.

1129
01:34:44,590 --> 01:34:46,020
Brunettes.

1130
01:34:47,590 --> 01:34:49,080
Redheads.

1131
01:34:51,800 --> 01:34:54,270
I keep the blondes in here.

1132
01:34:54,370 --> 01:34:56,930
It was yellow hair
you was looking for, sir?

1133
01:34:57,040 --> 01:34:58,400
Yes.

1134
01:35:29,470 --> 01:35:33,500
- That one there has the shade I need.
- Come, child.

1135
01:35:40,250 --> 01:35:43,740
Smile for the gentleman
and you shall have a sweetie.

1136
01:35:45,750 --> 01:35:48,020
Now, where shall I cut?

1137
01:35:49,420 --> 01:35:52,790
Not another word, Mr. Fogg,
or it will be your last.

1138
01:35:54,730 --> 01:35:59,600
Now, I leave you
to the mercy of your children.

1139
01:36:10,010 --> 01:36:13,340
I got him locked in.
But if he escapes, he'll go to the law.

1140
01:36:13,450 --> 01:36:15,680
- Then he won't escape.
- I don't know, Mr. Todd.

1141
01:36:15,780 --> 01:36:18,050
The Judge'll be here soon.

1142
01:36:19,620 --> 01:36:22,450
'Scuse me, sir. Gave me a fright.

1143
01:36:22,560 --> 01:36:25,550
Not my intention, good madam.
I assure you.

1144
01:36:26,330 --> 01:36:29,320
Though I am here on official business.

1145
01:36:30,000 --> 01:36:35,260
You see, there's been some complaints
about the stink from your chimney.

1146
01:36:35,370 --> 01:36:38,400
They say at night
it is something most foul.

1147
01:36:39,270 --> 01:36:42,370
Health regulations
and the general public welfare

1148
01:36:42,480 --> 01:36:44,380
naturally being my duty,

1149
01:36:44,480 --> 01:36:47,610
I'm afraid I'm gonna have to take a look

1150
01:36:50,480 --> 01:36:52,180
at your bakehouse.

1151
01:36:53,590 --> 01:36:55,080
Of course, sir.

1152
01:36:55,190 --> 01:36:58,850
But first, why don't you come upstairs?
Let me pamper you.

1153
01:37:00,630 --> 01:37:03,560
Much as I do appreciate
tonsorial doormen

1154
01:37:03,660 --> 01:37:06,130
I really ought to see
to my official obligations first.

1155
01:37:06,230 --> 01:37:08,220
I completely understand.

1156
01:37:11,610 --> 01:37:16,170
If you'll indulge me, sir,
what is that exotic aroma?

1157
01:37:19,150 --> 01:37:22,170
Me secret, is a touch of ambergris.

1158
01:37:23,550 --> 01:37:26,210
Dare I offer you something
a tad more appropriate

1159
01:37:26,320 --> 01:37:28,720
for a gentleman of your standing?

1160
01:37:28,820 --> 01:37:31,760
The ladies will greatly appreciate it, sir.

1161
01:37:34,630 --> 01:37:37,890
You're the expert in these matters.

1162
01:37:38,000 --> 01:37:39,930
Only take a moment.

1163
01:37:44,070 --> 01:37:46,560
Would you like a bit of bay rum, sir?

1164
01:37:46,670 --> 01:37:48,940
Bay rum is very bracing.

1165
01:38:54,770 --> 01:38:58,400
Let me out! Please, let me out!

1166
01:39:01,180 --> 01:39:02,810
Let me out!

1167
01:39:20,470 --> 01:39:21,630
Toby?

1168
01:39:23,440 --> 01:39:24,990
Where is he?

1169
01:39:29,110 --> 01:39:33,980
Toby, where are you, love?

1170
01:39:36,080 --> 01:39:37,340
Toby?

1171
01:39:41,320 --> 01:39:44,950
Nothing's gonna harm you

1172
01:39:45,060 --> 01:39:48,290
Not while I'm around

1173
01:39:48,400 --> 01:39:49,660
Toby?

1174
01:39:51,500 --> 01:39:53,760
Where are you hiding?

1175
01:39:55,300 --> 01:39:56,460
Toby?

1176
01:39:57,670 --> 01:40:00,870
Nothing's gonna harm you, darling

1177
01:40:03,380 --> 01:40:05,970
Not while I'm around

1178
01:40:10,020 --> 01:40:11,280
Toby?

1179
01:40:13,420 --> 01:40:14,850
Mr. Todd!

1180
01:40:16,890 --> 01:40:18,480
You wait for him here.

1181
01:40:18,590 --> 01:40:22,080
I'll return with a coach
in less than half an hour.

1182
01:40:22,200 --> 01:40:26,660
Don't worry. No one'll recognize you.
You're safe now.

1183
01:40:27,670 --> 01:40:32,500
Safe? So, we run away
and then all our dreams come true?

1184
01:40:33,610 --> 01:40:35,270
I hope so.

1185
01:40:36,080 --> 01:40:39,270
I've never had dreams. Only nightmares.

1186
01:40:40,280 --> 01:40:41,680
Johanna,

1187
01:40:42,420 --> 01:40:45,870
when we're free of this place
all the ghosts will go away.

1188
01:40:45,990 --> 01:40:49,420
No, Anthony. They never go away.

1189
01:40:50,490 --> 01:40:54,220
I'll be right back to you.
Half an hour and we'll be free.

1190
01:41:29,660 --> 01:41:32,290
Beadle! Beadle!

1191
01:41:33,500 --> 01:41:38,270
No good hiding, I saw you

1192
01:41:38,370 --> 01:41:43,330
Are you in there still, Beadle?
Beadle?

1193
01:41:43,440 --> 01:41:46,240
Beadle, dear Beadle?

1194
01:41:48,380 --> 01:41:51,510
Beadle deedle deedle
deedle deedle dumpling

1195
01:41:51,620 --> 01:41:53,810
Beadle dumpling...

1196
01:42:00,830 --> 01:42:03,850
Who are you?
What are you doing here?

1197
01:42:06,100 --> 01:42:07,590
Evil is here, sir.

1198
01:42:07,700 --> 01:42:12,300
The stink of evil, from below, from her!
Oh, she's the Devil's wife.

1199
01:42:12,410 --> 01:42:16,400
Beware her, sir.
She with no pity in her heart.

1200
01:42:18,410 --> 01:42:21,280
Don't I know you, mister?

1201
01:42:21,380 --> 01:42:22,850
Mr. Todd?

1202
01:42:34,290 --> 01:42:35,820
Where is she?

1203
01:42:37,260 --> 01:42:39,860
Below, Your Honor. With my neighbor.

1204
01:42:40,870 --> 01:42:44,430
Thank heavens
the sailor did not molest her.

1205
01:42:44,540 --> 01:42:49,100
Thank heavens, too,
she has seen the error of her ways.

1206
01:42:49,980 --> 01:42:52,240
- She has?
- Oh, yes.

1207
01:42:53,110 --> 01:42:55,410
Your lesson was well-learned.

1208
01:42:55,520 --> 01:42:59,610
She speaks only of you.
Longing for forgiveness.

1209
01:43:01,420 --> 01:43:03,580
Then she shall have it.

1210
01:43:04,660 --> 01:43:08,020
- She'll be here soon, you say?
- Yes.

1211
01:43:08,630 --> 01:43:10,600
Excellent, my friend.

1212
01:43:12,600 --> 01:43:14,260
How about a shave?

1213
01:43:15,670 --> 01:43:17,600
Sit, sir. Sit.

1214
01:43:20,610 --> 01:43:26,640
- Oh, pretty women
- Pretty women, yes

1215
01:43:26,750 --> 01:43:29,810
Johanna, Johanna

1216
01:43:29,920 --> 01:43:33,510
Pretty women
Pretty women are a wonder

1217
01:43:33,620 --> 01:43:35,210
Pretty women!

1218
01:43:35,320 --> 01:43:38,220
What we do for pretty women!

1219
01:43:38,320 --> 01:43:41,990
- Blowing out their candles
- Blowing out their candles

1220
01:43:42,100 --> 01:43:45,690
- Or combing out their hair
- Or combing out their hair

1221
01:43:45,800 --> 01:43:47,490
Then they leave

1222
01:43:47,600 --> 01:43:51,160
- Even when they leave
- Even when they leave you and vanish

1223
01:43:51,270 --> 01:43:54,170
- They still are there
- They somehow can still remain

1224
01:43:54,270 --> 01:43:59,210
- There with you, there
- They're there

1225
01:44:00,010 --> 01:44:03,610
How seldom it is
one meets a fellow spirit.

1226
01:44:03,720 --> 01:44:07,950
With fellow tastes in women, at least.

1227
01:44:08,790 --> 01:44:10,260
What's that?

1228
01:44:11,160 --> 01:44:14,060
The years, no doubt,
have changed me, sir.

1229
01:44:14,160 --> 01:44:17,060
But then, I suppose the face of a barber,

1230
01:44:17,160 --> 01:44:21,220
the face of a prisoner,
a dog, is not particularly memorable.

1231
01:44:27,970 --> 01:44:30,410
Benjamin Barker.

1232
01:44:30,740 --> 01:44:33,580
Benjamin Barker!

1233
01:45:11,420 --> 01:45:14,880
Rest now, my friend

1234
01:45:17,020 --> 01:45:21,260
Rest now forever

1235
01:45:22,730 --> 01:45:28,000
Sleep now the untroubled

1236
01:45:28,100 --> 01:45:33,660
Sleep of the angels

1237
01:45:44,850 --> 01:45:46,940
Come for a shave, have you, lad?

1238
01:45:47,050 --> 01:45:48,650
No, I...

1239
01:45:52,530 --> 01:45:55,290
Everyone needs a good shave.

1240
01:46:02,500 --> 01:46:04,560
Forget my face.

1241
01:46:08,410 --> 01:46:11,640
Die! God in heaven, die!

1242
01:46:25,490 --> 01:46:26,980
You.

1243
01:46:35,940 --> 01:46:37,730
Why did you scream?

1244
01:46:37,840 --> 01:46:40,810
He was clutching onto me dress,
but he's finished now.

1245
01:46:40,910 --> 01:46:43,340
I'll take care of it. Open the door.

1246
01:46:43,440 --> 01:46:45,740
Open the door, I said.

1247
01:47:39,930 --> 01:47:42,590
"Don't I know you?" she said.

1248
01:47:52,350 --> 01:47:54,180
You knew she lived.

1249
01:47:56,150 --> 01:47:58,410
I was only thinking of you.

1250
01:48:02,020 --> 01:48:03,990
You lied to me.

1251
01:48:04,090 --> 01:48:07,650
No, no, not lied at all
No, I never lied

1252
01:48:07,760 --> 01:48:09,420
- Lucy...
- Said she took a poison

1253
01:48:09,530 --> 01:48:11,430
she did, never said that she died

1254
01:48:11,530 --> 01:48:13,730
- I've come home again
- Poor thing, she lived

1255
01:48:13,830 --> 01:48:15,100
But it left her weak in the head

1256
01:48:15,200 --> 01:48:17,670
All she did for months
was just lie there in bed

1257
01:48:17,770 --> 01:48:19,140
Should've been in hospital

1258
01:48:19,240 --> 01:48:21,970
Wound up in Bedlam instead
Poor thing!

1259
01:48:22,080 --> 01:48:24,310
- Better you should think she was dead
- Oh, my God!

1260
01:48:24,410 --> 01:48:27,280
Yes, I lied 'cause I love you!

1261
01:48:27,380 --> 01:48:30,110
- I'd be twice the wife she was!
- Lucy...

1262
01:48:30,220 --> 01:48:32,510
- I love you!
- What have I done?

1263
01:48:32,620 --> 01:48:35,820
Could that thing have
cared for you like me?

1264
01:48:35,920 --> 01:48:38,980
Mrs. Lovett, you're a bloody wonder
Eminently practical

1265
01:48:39,090 --> 01:48:41,860
And yet appropriate as always
As you've said repeatedly

1266
01:48:41,960 --> 01:48:43,620
There's little point in dwelling
on the past

